37 //////////////////// Private helpers.
38 
39 #define LOAD_KIND(kind) \
40  Int32Constant(static_cast<intptr_t>(LoadHandler::Kind::kind))
41 #define STORE_KIND(kind) \
42  Int32Constant(static_cast<intptr_t>(StoreHandler::Kind::kind))
43 
44 // Loads dataX field from the DataHandler object.
45 TNode<MaybeObject> AccessorAssembler::LoadHandlerDataField(
46  TNode<DataHandler> handler, int data_index) {
47 #ifdef DEBUG
48  TNode<Map> handler_map = LoadMap(handler);
49  TNode<Uint16T> instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(handler_map);
50 #endif
51  CSA_DCHECK(this,
52  Word32Or(InstanceTypeEqual(instance_type, LOAD_HANDLER_TYPE),
53  InstanceTypeEqual(instance_type, STORE_HANDLER_TYPE)));
54  // data_index is 1-indexed, so subtract one to make it 0-indexed.
55  data_index -= 1;
56  CHECK_GE(data_index, 0);
57  CHECK_LT(data_index, 3);
58  int offset = DataHandler::OffsetOf(data_index);
59  CSA_DCHECK(this, UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(
60  LoadMapInstanceSizeInWords(handler_map),
61  IntPtrConstant(DataHandler::SizeFor(data_index + 1) /
62  kTaggedSize)));
63  return LoadMaybeWeakObjectField(handler, offset);
64 }
65 
66 TNode<HeapObjectReference> AccessorAssembler::TryMonomorphicCase(
67  TNode<TaggedIndex> slot, TNode<FeedbackVector> vector,
68  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map, Label* if_handler,
69  TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler, Label* if_miss) {
70  Comment("TryMonomorphicCase");
71  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, var_handler->rep());
72 
73  // TODO(ishell): add helper class that hides offset computations for a series
74  // of loads.
75  int32_t header_size =
76  FeedbackVector::kRawFeedbackSlotsOffset - kHeapObjectTag;
77  // Adding |header_size| with a separate IntPtrAdd rather than passing it
78  // into ElementOffsetFromIndex() allows it to be folded into a single
79  // [base, index, offset] indirect memory access on x64.
80  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = ElementOffsetFromIndex(slot, HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
81  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = CAST(Load<MaybeObject>(
82  vector, IntPtrAdd(offset, IntPtrConstant(header_size))));
83 
84  // Try to quickly handle the monomorphic case without knowing for sure
85  // if we have a weak reference in feedback.
86  CSA_DCHECK(this,
87  IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(weak_lookup_start_object_map)));
88  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(feedback, weak_lookup_start_object_map), if_miss);
89 
90  TNode<MaybeObject> handler = UncheckedCast<MaybeObject>(
91  Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), vector,
92  IntPtrAdd(offset, IntPtrConstant(header_size + kTaggedSize))));
93 
94  *var_handler = handler;
95  Goto(if_handler);
96  return feedback;
97 }
98 
99 void AccessorAssembler::HandlePolymorphicCase(
100  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map,
101  TNode<WeakFixedArray> feedback, Label* if_handler,
102  TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler, Label* if_miss) {
103  Comment("HandlePolymorphicCase");
104  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, var_handler->rep());
105 
106  // Iterate {feedback} array.
107  const int kEntrySize = 2;
108 
109  // Load the {feedback} array length.
110  TNode<Int32T> length =
111  Signed(LoadAndUntagWeakFixedArrayLengthAsUint32(feedback));
112  CSA_DCHECK(this, Int32LessThanOrEqual(Int32Constant(kEntrySize), length));
113 
114  // This is a hand-crafted loop that iterates backwards and only compares
115  // against zero at the end, since we already know that we will have at least a
116  // single entry in the {feedback} array anyways.
117  TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_index, Int32Sub(length, Int32Constant(kEntrySize)));
118  Label loop(this, &var_index), loop_next(this);
119  Goto(&loop);
120  BIND(&loop);
121  {
122  TNode<IntPtrT> index = ChangePositiveInt32ToIntPtr(var_index.value());
123  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_cached_map =
124  LoadWeakFixedArrayElement(feedback, index);
125  CSA_DCHECK(this,
126  IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(weak_lookup_start_object_map)));
127  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(maybe_cached_map, weak_lookup_start_object_map),
128  &loop_next);
129 
130  // Found, now call handler.
131  TNode<MaybeObject> handler =
132  LoadWeakFixedArrayElement(feedback, index, kTaggedSize);
133  *var_handler = handler;
134  Goto(if_handler);
135 
136  BIND(&loop_next);
137  var_index = Int32Sub(var_index.value(), Int32Constant(kEntrySize));
138  Branch(Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(var_index.value(), Int32Constant(0)), &loop,
139  if_miss);
140  }
141 }
142 
143 void AccessorAssembler::TryMegaDOMCase(TNode<Object> lookup_start_object,
144  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
145  TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler,
146  TNode<Object> vector,
147  TNode<TaggedIndex> slot, Label* miss,
148  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
149  // Check if the receiver is a JS_API_OBJECT
150  GotoIfNot(IsJSApiObjectMap(lookup_start_object_map), miss);
151 
152  // Check if receiver requires access check
153  GotoIf(IsSetWord32<Map::Bits1::IsAccessCheckNeededBit>(
154  LoadMapBitField(lookup_start_object_map)),
155  miss);
156 
157  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot),
158  MegaDOMSymbolConstant()));
159 
160  // In some cases, we load the
161  TNode<MegaDomHandler> handler;
162  if (var_handler->IsBound()) {
163  handler = CAST(var_handler->value());
164  } else {
165  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_handler =
166  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot, kTaggedSize);
167  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsStrong(maybe_handler));
168  handler = CAST(maybe_handler);
169  }
170 
171  // Check if dom protector cell is still valid
172  GotoIf(IsMegaDOMProtectorCellInvalid(), miss);
173 
174  // Load the getter
175  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_getter = LoadMegaDomHandlerAccessor(handler);
176  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_getter));
177  TNode<FunctionTemplateInfo> getter =
178  CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_getter, miss));
179 
180  // Load the accessor context
181  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_context = LoadMegaDomHandlerContext(handler);
182  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_context));
183  TNode<Context> context = CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_context, miss));
184 
185  // TODO(gsathya): This builtin throws an exception on interface check fail but
186  // we should miss to the runtime.
187  TNode<Context> caller_context = context;
188  exit_point->Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_Generic,
189  context, getter, Int32Constant(1),
190  caller_context, lookup_start_object));
191 }
192 
193 void AccessorAssembler::TryEnumeratedKeyedLoad(
194  const LoadICParameters* p, TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
195  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
196  if (!p->IsEnumeratedKeyedLoad()) return;
197  Label no_enum_cache(this);
198  // |p->cache_type()| comes from the outer loop's ForIn state.
199  GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(p->cache_type(), lookup_start_object_map),
200  &no_enum_cache);
201 
202  // Use field index in EnumCache.
203  TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
204  LoadMapDescriptors(lookup_start_object_map);
205  TNode<EnumCache> enum_cache = LoadObjectField<EnumCache>(
206  descriptors, DescriptorArray::kEnumCacheOffset);
207  TNode<FixedArray> enum_keys =
208  LoadObjectField<FixedArray>(enum_cache, EnumCache::kKeysOffset);
209  // |p->enum_index()| comes from the outer loop's ForIn state.
210  TNode<Object> key = LoadFixedArrayElement(enum_keys, p->enum_index());
211  // Check if |p->name()| matches the key in enum cache. |p->name()| is the
212  // "each" variable of a for-in loop, but it can be modified by debugger or
213  // other bytecodes.
214  GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(key, p->name()), &no_enum_cache);
215  TNode<FixedArray> enum_indices =
216  LoadObjectField<FixedArray>(enum_cache, EnumCache::kIndicesOffset);
217  // Check if we have enum indices available.
218  GotoIf(IsEmptyFixedArray(enum_indices), &no_enum_cache);
219  TNode<Int32T> field_index =
220  SmiToInt32(CAST(LoadFixedArrayElement(enum_indices, p->enum_index())));
221 
222  TVARIABLE(Object, result);
223  Label if_double(this, Label::kDeferred), done(this, &result);
224  // Check if field is a mutable double field.
225  uint32_t kIsMutableDoubleFieldMask = 1;
226  GotoIf(IsSetWord32(field_index, kIsMutableDoubleFieldMask), &if_double);
227 
228  TNode<Int32T> zero = Int32Constant(0);
229  {
230  Label if_outofobject(this);
231  // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
232  GotoIf(Int32LessThan(field_index, zero), &if_outofobject);
233 
234  // The field is located in the {object} itself.
235  {
236  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(
237  Int32Add(Word32Shl(field_index, Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)),
238  Int32Constant(JSObject::kHeaderSize))));
239  result =
240  LoadObjectField(CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), offset);
241  Goto(&done);
242  }
243 
244  // The field is located in the properties backing store of {object}.
245  // The {index} is equal to the negated out of property index plus 1.
246  BIND(&if_outofobject);
247  {
248  TNode<PropertyArray> properties = CAST(LoadFastProperties(
249  CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), true));
250  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(Int32Add(
251  Word32Shl(Int32Sub(zero, field_index),
252  Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2 - 1)),
253  Int32Constant(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize))));
254  result = LoadObjectField(properties, offset);
255  Goto(&done);
256  }
257  }
258 
259  // The field is a Double field, either unboxed in the object on 64-bit
260  // architectures, or a mutable HeapNumber.
261  BIND(&if_double);
262  {
263  TVARIABLE(Object, field);
264  Label loaded_field(this, &field), if_outofobject(this);
265  field_index = Word32Sar(field_index, Int32Constant(1));
266  // Check if field is in-object or out-of-object.
267  GotoIf(Int32LessThan(field_index, zero), &if_outofobject);
268 
269  // The field is located in the {object} itself.
270  {
271  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(
272  Int32Add(Word32Shl(field_index, Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
273  Int32Constant(JSObject::kHeaderSize))));
274  field =
275  LoadObjectField(CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), offset);
276  Goto(&loaded_field);
277  }
278 
279  BIND(&if_outofobject);
280  {
281  TNode<PropertyArray> properties = CAST(LoadFastProperties(
282  CAST(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object()), true));
283  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(ChangeUint32ToWord(Int32Add(
284  Word32Shl(Int32Sub(zero, field_index),
285  Int32Constant(kTaggedSizeLog2)),
286  Int32Constant(OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray) - kTaggedSize))));
287  field = LoadObjectField(properties, offset);
288  Goto(&loaded_field);
289  }
290 
291  BIND(&loaded_field);
292  {
293  // We may have transitioned in-place away from double, so check that
294  // this is a HeapNumber -- otherwise the load is fine and we don't need
295  // to copy anything anyway.
296  Label if_not_double(this);
297  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(field.value()), &if_not_double);
298 
299  TNode<HeapObject> double_field = CAST(field.value());
300  TNode<Map> field_map = LoadMap(double_field);
301  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(field_map, HeapNumberMapConstant()),
302  &if_not_double);
303 
304  TNode<Float64T> value = LoadHeapNumberValue(double_field);
305  result = AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(value);
306  Goto(&done);
307 
308  BIND(&if_not_double);
309  {
310  result = field.value();
311  Goto(&done);
312  }
313  }
314  }
315 
316  BIND(&done);
317  { exit_point->Return(result.value()); }
318 
319  BIND(&no_enum_cache);
320 }
321 
322 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICHandlerCase(
323  const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss,
324  ExitPoint* exit_point, ICMode ic_mode, OnNonExistent on_nonexistent,
325  ElementSupport support_elements, LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
326  Comment("have_handler");
327 
328  TVARIABLE(Object, var_holder, p->lookup_start_object());
329  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_smi_handler, handler);
330 
331  Label if_smi_handler(this, {&var_holder, &var_smi_handler});
332  Label try_proto_handler(this, Label::kDeferred),
333  call_code_handler(this, Label::kDeferred),
334  call_getter(this, Label::kDeferred);
335 
336  Branch(TaggedIsSmi(handler), &if_smi_handler, &try_proto_handler);
337 
338  BIND(&try_proto_handler);
339  {
340  GotoIf(IsWeakOrCleared(handler), &call_getter);
341  GotoIf(IsCode(CAST(handler)), &call_code_handler);
342  HandleLoadICProtoHandler(p, CAST(handler), &var_holder, &var_smi_handler,
343  &if_smi_handler, miss, exit_point, ic_mode,
344  access_mode);
345  }
346 
347  // |handler| is a Smi, encoding what to do. See SmiHandler methods
348  // for the encoding format.
349  BIND(&if_smi_handler);
350  {
351  HandleLoadICSmiHandlerCase(
352  p, var_holder.value(), CAST(var_smi_handler.value()), handler, miss,
353  exit_point, ic_mode, on_nonexistent, support_elements, access_mode);
354  }
355 
356  BIND(&call_getter);
357  {
358  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
359  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
360  } else {
361  TNode<HeapObject> strong_handler = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(handler, miss);
362  TNode<JSFunction> getter =
363  CAST(LoadAccessorPairGetter(CAST(strong_handler)));
364 
365  ConvertReceiverMode mode =
366  p->lookup_start_object() == p->receiver()
367  // LoadIC case: the receiver is definitely not null or undefined.
368  ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined
369  // LoadSuperIC case: the receiver might be anything.
370  : ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
371  exit_point->Return(
372  CallFunction(p->context(), getter, mode, p->receiver()));
373  }
374  }
375 
376  BIND(&call_code_handler);
377  {
378  TNode<Code> code_handler = CAST(handler);
379  exit_point->ReturnCallStub(LoadWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler,
380  p->context(), p->lookup_start_object(),
381  p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
382  }
383 }
384 
385 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadCallbackProperty(
386  const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<JSObject> holder,
387  TNode<Word32T> handler_word, ExitPoint* exit_point) {
388  Comment("native_data_property_load");
389  TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor =
390  Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
391 
392  TNode<AccessorInfo> accessor_info =
393  CAST(LoadDescriptorValue(LoadMap(holder), descriptor));
394 
395  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiGetter, p->context(),
396  p->receiver(), holder, accessor_info);
397 }
398 
399 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadAccessor(
400  const LazyLoadICParameters* p,
401  TNode<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info,
402  TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<DataHandler> handler,
403  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind, ExitPoint* exit_point) {
404  Comment("api_getter");
405  // Context is stored either in data2 or data3 field depending on whether
406  // the access check is enabled for this handler or not.
407  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_context = Select<MaybeObject>(
408  IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits>(
409  handler_word),
410  [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 3); },
411  [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 2); });
412 
413  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_context));
414  CSA_CHECK(this, IsNotCleared(maybe_context));
415  TNode<HeapObject> context = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_context);
416  TNode<Int32T> argc = Int32Constant(0);
417  TNode<Context> caller_context = p->context();
418  exit_point->Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackGeneric, context,
419  argc, caller_context, function_template_info,
420  p->receiver()));
421 }
422 
423 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadField(TNode<JSObject> holder,
424  TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
425  TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
426  Label* rebox_double, Label* miss,
427  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
428  Comment("LoadField");
429  TNode<IntPtrT> index =
430  Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::FieldIndexBits>(handler_word));
431  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = IntPtrMul(index, IntPtrConstant(kTaggedSize));
432 
433  TNode<BoolT> is_inobject =
434  IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsInobjectBits>(handler_word);
435  TNode<HeapObject> property_storage = Select<HeapObject>(
436  is_inobject, [&]() { return holder; },
437  [&]() { return LoadFastProperties(holder, true); });
438 
439  Label is_double(this);
440  TNode<Object> value = LoadObjectField(property_storage, offset);
441  GotoIf(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsDoubleBits>(handler_word), &is_double);
442  exit_point->Return(value);
443 
444  BIND(&is_double);
445  // This is not an "old" Smi value from before a Smi->Double transition.
446  // Rather, it's possible that since the last update of this IC, the Double
447  // field transitioned to a Tagged field, and was then assigned a Smi.
448  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
449  GotoIfNot(IsHeapNumber(CAST(value)), miss);
450  *var_double_value = LoadHeapNumberValue(CAST(value));
451  Goto(rebox_double);
452 }
453 
454 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
455 
456 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadWasmField(
457  TNode<WasmObject> holder, TNode<Int32T> wasm_value_type,
458  TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset, TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
459  Label* rebox_double, ExitPoint* exit_point) {
460  Label type_I8(this), type_I16(this), type_I32(this), type_U32(this),
461  type_I64(this), type_U64(this), type_F32(this), type_F64(this),
462  type_Ref(this), unsupported_type(this, Label::kDeferred),
463  unexpected_type(this, Label::kDeferred);
464  Label* wasm_value_type_labels[] = {
465  &type_I8, &type_I16, &type_I32, &type_U32, &type_I64,
466  &type_F32, &type_F64, &type_Ref, &type_Ref, &unsupported_type};
467  int32_t wasm_value_types[] = {
468  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI8),
469  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI16),
470  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI32),
471  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kU32),
472  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kI64),
473  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kF32),
474  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kF64),
475  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kRef),
476  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kRefNull),
477  // TODO(v8:11804): support the following value types.
478  static_cast<int32_t>(WasmValueType::kS128)};
479  const size_t kWasmValueTypeCount =
480  static_cast<size_t>(WasmValueType::kNumTypes);
481  DCHECK_EQ(kWasmValueTypeCount, arraysize(wasm_value_types));
482  DCHECK_EQ(kWasmValueTypeCount, arraysize(wasm_value_type_labels));
483 
484  Switch(wasm_value_type, &unexpected_type, wasm_value_types,
485  wasm_value_type_labels, kWasmValueTypeCount);
486  BIND(&type_I8);
487  {
488  Comment("type_I8");
489  TNode<Int32T> value = LoadObjectField<Int8T>(holder, field_offset);
490  exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(value));
491  }
492  BIND(&type_I16);
493  {
494  Comment("type_I16");
495  TNode<Int32T> value = LoadObjectField<Int16T>(holder, field_offset);
496  exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(value));
497  }
498  BIND(&type_I32);
499  {
500  Comment("type_I32");
501  TNode<Int32T> value = LoadObjectField<Int32T>(holder, field_offset);
502  exit_point->Return(ChangeInt32ToTagged(value));
503  }
504  BIND(&type_U32);
505  {
506  Comment("type_U32");
507  TNode<Uint32T> value = LoadObjectField<Uint32T>(holder, field_offset);
508  exit_point->Return(ChangeUint32ToTagged(value));
509  }
510  BIND(&type_I64);
511  {
512  Comment("type_I64");
513  TNode<RawPtrT> data_pointer =
514  ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(BitcastTaggedToWord(holder));
515  TNode<BigInt> value = LoadFixedBigInt64ArrayElementAsTagged(
516  data_pointer,
517  Signed(IntPtrSub(field_offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
518  exit_point->Return(value);
519  }
520  BIND(&type_F32);
521  {
522  Comment("type_F32");
523  TNode<Float32T> value = LoadObjectField<Float32T>(holder, field_offset);
524  *var_double_value = ChangeFloat32ToFloat64(value);
525  Goto(rebox_double);
526  }
527  BIND(&type_F64);
528  {
529  Comment("type_F64");
530  TNode<Float64T> value = LoadObjectField<Float64T>(holder, field_offset);
531  *var_double_value = value;
532  Goto(rebox_double);
533  }
534  BIND(&type_Ref);
535  {
536  Comment("type_Ref");
537  TNode<Object> value = LoadObjectField(holder, field_offset);
538  exit_point->Return(value);
539  }
540  BIND(&unsupported_type);
541  {
542  Print("Not supported Wasm field type");
543  Unreachable();
544  }
545  BIND(&unexpected_type);
546  { Unreachable(); }
547 }
548 
549 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadWasmField(
550  TNode<WasmObject> holder, TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
551  TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value, Label* rebox_double,
552  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
553  Comment("LoadWasmField");
554  TNode<Int32T> wasm_value_type =
555  Signed(DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::WasmFieldTypeBits>(handler_word));
556  TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset = Signed(
557  DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::WasmFieldOffsetBits>(handler_word));
558 
559  HandleLoadWasmField(holder, wasm_value_type, field_offset, var_double_value,
560  rebox_double, exit_point);
561 }
562 
563 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

575 
576 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICSmiHandlerCase(
577  const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<Object> holder, TNode<Smi> smi_handler,
578  TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point,
579  ICMode ic_mode, OnNonExistent on_nonexistent,
580  ElementSupport support_elements, LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
581  TVARIABLE(Float64T, var_double_value);
582  Label rebox_double(this, &var_double_value);
583 
584  TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(smi_handler);
585  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
586  DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
587 
588  if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
589  Label if_element(this), if_transition(this), if_indexed_string(this),
590  if_property(this), if_hole(this), unimplemented_elements_kind(this),
591  if_oob(this, Label::kDeferred), try_string_to_array_index(this),
592  emit_element_load(this);
593  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_intptr_index);
594  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kElement)), &if_element);
595  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kElementWithTransition)),
596  &if_transition);
597 
598  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
599  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32NotEqual(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kIndexedString)));
600  Goto(&if_property);
601  } else {
602  Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kIndexedString)),
603  &if_indexed_string, &if_property);
604  }
605 
606  BIND(&if_element);
607  {
608  Comment("element_load");
609  // TODO(ishell): implement
610  CSA_DCHECK(this,
611  IsClearWord32<LoadHandler::IsWasmArrayBits>(handler_word));
612  TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_instance_type);
613  TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index = TryToIntptr(
614  p->name(), &try_string_to_array_index, &var_instance_type);
615  var_intptr_index = intptr_index;
616  Goto(&emit_element_load);
617 
618  BIND(&try_string_to_array_index);
619  {
620  GotoIfNot(IsStringInstanceType(var_instance_type.value()), miss);
621 
622  TNode<ExternalReference> function = ExternalConstant(
623  ExternalReference::string_to_array_index_function());
624  TNode<Int32T> result = UncheckedCast<Int32T>(
625  CallCFunction(function, MachineType::Int32(),
626  std::make_pair(MachineType::AnyTagged(), p->name())));
627  GotoIf(Word32Equal(Int32Constant(-1), result), miss);
628  CSA_DCHECK(this, Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(result, Int32Constant(0)));
629  var_intptr_index = ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(result);
630 
631  Goto(&emit_element_load);
632  }
633 
634  BIND(&emit_element_load);
635  {
636  TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition =
637  IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsJsArrayBits>(handler_word);
638  TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind =
639  DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::ElementsKindBits>(handler_word);
640  EmitElementLoad(CAST(holder), elements_kind, var_intptr_index.value(),
641  is_jsarray_condition, &if_hole, &rebox_double,
642  &var_double_value, &unimplemented_elements_kind,
643  &if_oob, miss, exit_point, access_mode);
644  }
645  }
646 
647  BIND(&if_transition);
648  {
649  TNode<Uint32T> elements_kind =
650  DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::ElementsKindBits>(handler_word);
651  CallRuntime(Runtime::kTransitionElementsKindWithKind, p->context(),
652  p->receiver(), SmiFromUint32(elements_kind));
653  Goto(&if_element);
654  }
655 
656  BIND(&unimplemented_elements_kind);
657  {
658  // Smi handlers should only be installed for supported elements kinds.
659  // Crash if we get here.
660  DebugBreak();
661  Goto(miss);
662  }
663 
664  BIND(&if_oob);
665  {
666  Comment("out of bounds elements access");
667  Label return_undefined(this);
668 
669  // Check if we're allowed to handle OOB accesses.
670  TNode<BoolT> allow_out_of_bounds =
671  IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowOutOfBoundsBits>(handler_word);
672  GotoIfNot(allow_out_of_bounds, miss);
673 
674  // Negative indices aren't valid array indices (according to
675  // the ECMAScript specification), and are stored as properties
676  // in V8, not elements. So we cannot handle them here, except
677  // in case of typed arrays, where integer indexed properties
678  // aren't looked up in the prototype chain.
679  GotoIf(IsJSTypedArray(CAST(holder)), &return_undefined);
680  if (Is64()) {
681  GotoIfNot(
682  UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(var_intptr_index.value(),
683  IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex)),
684  miss);
685  } else {
686  GotoIf(IntPtrLessThan(var_intptr_index.value(), IntPtrConstant(0)),
687  miss);
688  }
689 
690  // For all other receivers we need to check that the prototype chain
691  // doesn't contain any elements.
692  BranchIfPrototypesHaveNoElements(LoadMap(CAST(holder)), &return_undefined,
693  miss);
694 
695  BIND(&return_undefined);
696  exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas
697  ? TNode<Object>(FalseConstant())
698  : TNode<Object>(UndefinedConstant()));
699  }
700 
701  BIND(&if_hole);
702  {
703  Comment("read hole and convert to undefined");
704 
705  GotoIfNot(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowHandlingHole>(handler_word),
706  miss);
707  GotoIf(IsNoElementsProtectorCellInvalid(), miss);
708  exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas
709  ? TNode<Object>(FalseConstant())
710  : TNode<Object>(UndefinedConstant()));
711  }
712 
713  if (access_mode != LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
714  BIND(&if_indexed_string);
715  {
716  Label if_oob_string(this, Label::kDeferred);
717 
718  Comment("indexed string");
719  TNode<String> string_holder = CAST(holder);
720  TNode<IntPtrT> index = TryToIntptr(p->name(), miss);
721  TNode<UintPtrT> length =
722  Unsigned(LoadStringLengthAsWord(string_holder));
723  GotoIf(UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(index, length), &if_oob_string);
724  TNode<Int32T> code = StringCharCodeAt(string_holder, Unsigned(index));
725  TNode<String> result = StringFromSingleCharCode(code);
726  Return(result);
727 
728  BIND(&if_oob_string);
729  if (Is64()) {
730  // Indices >= 4294967295 are stored as named properties; handle them
731  // in the runtime.
732  GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(
733  index, IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex)),
734  miss);
735  } else {
736  GotoIf(IntPtrLessThan(index, IntPtrConstant(0)), miss);
737  }
738  TNode<BoolT> allow_out_of_bounds =
739  IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowOutOfBoundsBits>(handler_word);
740  GotoIfNot(allow_out_of_bounds, miss);
741  GotoIf(IsNoElementsProtectorCellInvalid(), miss);
742  Return(UndefinedConstant());
743  }
744  }
745 
746  BIND(&if_property);
747  Comment("property_load");
748  }
749 
750  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
751  HandleLoadICSmiHandlerHasNamedCase(p, holder, handler_kind, miss,
752  exit_point, ic_mode);
753  } else {
754  HandleLoadICSmiHandlerLoadNamedCase(
755  p, holder, handler_kind, handler_word, &rebox_double, &var_double_value,
756  handler, miss, exit_point, ic_mode, on_nonexistent, support_elements);
757  }
758 }
759 
760 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICSmiHandlerLoadNamedCase(
761  const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<Object> holder,
762  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind, TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
763  Label* rebox_double, TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
764  TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point,
765  ICMode ic_mode, OnNonExistent on_nonexistent,
766  ElementSupport support_elements) {
767  Label constant(this), field(this), normal(this, Label::kDeferred),
768  slow(this, Label::kDeferred), interceptor(this, Label::kDeferred),
769  nonexistent(this), accessor(this, Label::kDeferred),
770  global(this, Label::kDeferred), module_export(this, Label::kDeferred),
771  proxy(this, Label::kDeferred),
772  native_data_property(this, Label::kDeferred),
773  api_getter(this, Label::kDeferred), generic(this, Label::kDeferred);
774 
775  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kField)), &field);
776 
777  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kConstantFromPrototype)),
778  &constant);
779 
780  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNonExistent)), &nonexistent);
781 
782  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNormal)), &normal);
783 
784  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kAccessorFromPrototype)),
785  &accessor);
786 
787  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
788  &native_data_property);
789 
790  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetter)), &api_getter);
791 
792  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kGlobal)), &global);
793 
794  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kSlow)), &slow);
795 
796  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kProxy)), &proxy);
797 
798  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kModuleExport)), &module_export);
799 
800  Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kInterceptor)), &interceptor,
801  &generic);
802 
803  BIND(&field);
804  {
805 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
806  Label is_wasm_field(this);
807  GotoIf(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::IsWasmStructBits>(handler_word),
808  &is_wasm_field);
809 #else
810  CSA_DCHECK(this,
811  IsClearWord32<LoadHandler::IsWasmStructBits>(handler_word));
812 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
813 
814  HandleLoadField(CAST(holder), handler_word, var_double_value, rebox_double,
815  miss, exit_point);
816 
817 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
818  BIND(&is_wasm_field);
819  HandleLoadWasmField(CAST(holder), handler_word, var_double_value,
820  rebox_double, exit_point);
821 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
822  }
823 
824  BIND(&nonexistent);
825  // This is a handler for a load of a non-existent value.
826  if (on_nonexistent == OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError) {
827  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowReferenceError, p->context(),
828  p->name());
829  } else {
830  DCHECK_EQ(OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined, on_nonexistent);
831  exit_point->Return(UndefinedConstant());
832  }
833 
834  BIND(&constant);
835  {
836  Comment("constant_load");
837  exit_point->Return(holder);
838  }
839 
840  BIND(&normal);
841  {
842  Comment("load_normal");
843  TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
844  CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(holder)));
845  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
846  Label found(this, &var_name_index);
847  NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
848  &found, &var_name_index, miss);
849  BIND(&found);
850  {
851  TVARIABLE(Uint32T, var_details);
852  TVARIABLE(Object, var_value);
853  LoadPropertyFromDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(
854  properties, var_name_index.value(), &var_details, &var_value);
855  TNode<Object> value = CallGetterIfAccessor(
856  var_value.value(), CAST(holder), var_details.value(), p->context(),
857  p->receiver(), p->name(), miss);
858  exit_point->Return(value);
859  }
860  }
861 
862  BIND(&accessor);
863  {
864  Comment("accessor_load");
865  // The "holder" slot (data1) in the from-prototype LoadHandler is instead
866  // directly the getter function.
867  TNode<HeapObject> getter = CAST(holder);
868  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsCallable(getter));
869 
870  exit_point->Return(Call(p->context(), getter, p->receiver()));
871  }
872 
873  BIND(&native_data_property);
874  HandleLoadCallbackProperty(p, CAST(holder), handler_word, exit_point);
875 
876  BIND(&api_getter);
877  {
878  if (p->receiver() != p->lookup_start_object()) {
879  // Force super ICs using API getters into the slow path, so that we get
880  // the correct receiver checks.
881  Goto(&slow);
882  } else {
883  HandleLoadAccessor(p, CAST(holder), handler_word, CAST(handler),
884  handler_kind, exit_point);
885  }
886  }
887 
888  BIND(&proxy);
889  {
890  // TODO(mythria): LoadGlobals don't use this path. LoadGlobals need special
891  // handling with proxies which is currently not supported by builtins. So
892  // for such cases, we should install a slow path and never reach here. Fix
893  // it to not generate this for LoadGlobals.
894  CSA_DCHECK(this,
895  WordNotEqual(IntPtrConstant(static_cast<int>(on_nonexistent)),
896  IntPtrConstant(static_cast<int>(
897  OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError))));
898  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
899  TVARIABLE(Name, var_unique);
900 
901  Label if_index(this), if_unique_name(this),
902  to_name_failed(this, Label::kDeferred);
903 
904  if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
905  DCHECK_NE(on_nonexistent, OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError);
906 
907  TryToName(p->name(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name, &var_unique,
908  &to_name_failed);
909 
910  BIND(&if_unique_name);
911  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxyGetProperty, p->context(),
912  holder, var_unique.value(), p->receiver(),
913  SmiConstant(on_nonexistent));
914 
915  BIND(&if_index);
916  // TODO(mslekova): introduce TryToName that doesn't try to compute
917  // the intptr index value
918  Goto(&to_name_failed);
919 
920  BIND(&to_name_failed);
921  // TODO(duongn): use GetPropertyWithReceiver builtin once
922  // |lookup_element_in_holder| supports elements.
923  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kGetPropertyWithReceiver,
924  p->context(), holder, p->name(),
925  p->receiver(), SmiConstant(on_nonexistent));
926  } else {
927  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxyGetProperty, p->context(),
928  holder, p->name(), p->receiver(),
929  SmiConstant(on_nonexistent));
930  }
931  }
932 
933  BIND(&global);
934  {
935  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsPropertyCell(CAST(holder)));
936  // Ensure the property cell doesn't contain the hole.
937  TNode<Object> value =
938  LoadObjectField(CAST(holder), PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
939  TNode<Uint32T> details = Unsigned(LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(
940  CAST(holder), PropertyCell::kPropertyDetailsRawOffset));
941  GotoIf(IsPropertyCellHole(value), miss);
942 
943  exit_point->Return(CallGetterIfAccessor(value, CAST(holder), details,
944  p->context(), p->receiver(),
945  p->name(), miss));
946  }
947 
948  BIND(&interceptor);
949  {
950  Comment("load_interceptor");
951  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadPropertyWithInterceptor,
952  p->context(), p->name(), p->receiver(),
953  holder, p->slot(), p->vector());
954  }
955  BIND(&slow);
956  {
957  Comment("load_slow");
958  if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
959  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadGlobalIC_Slow, p->context(),
960  p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
961 
962  } else {
963  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kGetProperty, p->context(),
964  p->lookup_start_object(), p->name(),
965  p->receiver());
966  }
967  }
968 
969  BIND(&generic);
970  {
971  Comment("load_generic");
972  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic,
973  p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(),
974  p->slot(), p->vector());
975  }
976 
977  BIND(&module_export);
978  {
979  Comment("module export");
980  TNode<UintPtrT> index =
981  DecodeWordFromWord32<LoadHandler::ExportsIndexBits>(handler_word);
982  TNode<Module> module =
983  LoadObjectField<Module>(CAST(holder), JSModuleNamespace::kModuleOffset);
984  TNode<ObjectHashTable> exports =
985  LoadObjectField<ObjectHashTable>(module, Module::kExportsOffset);
986  TNode<Cell> cell = CAST(LoadFixedArrayElement(exports, index));
987  // The handler is only installed for exports that exist.
988  TNode<Object> value = LoadCellValue(cell);
989  Label is_the_hole(this, Label::kDeferred);
990  GotoIf(IsTheHole(value), &is_the_hole);
991  exit_point->Return(value);
992 
993  BIND(&is_the_hole);
994  {
995  TNode<Smi> message = SmiConstant(MessageTemplate::kNotDefined);
996  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowReferenceError, p->context(),
997  message, p->name());
998  }
999  }
1000 
1001  BIND(rebox_double);
1002  {
1003 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1004  Label if_not_undefined(this);
1005  GotoIfNot(IsDoubleUndefined(var_double_value->value()), &if_not_undefined);
1006  GotoIfNot(IsSetWord32<LoadHandler::AllowHandlingHole>(handler_word), miss);
1007  exit_point->Return(UndefinedConstant());
1008 
1009  BIND(&if_not_undefined);
1010 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
1011  exit_point->Return(AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(var_double_value->value()));
1012  }
1013 }
1014 
1015 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICSmiHandlerHasNamedCase(
1016  const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<Object> holder,
1017  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point,
1018  ICMode ic_mode) {
1019  Label return_true(this), return_false(this), return_lookup(this),
1020  normal(this), global(this), slow(this);
1021 
1022  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kField)), &return_true);
1023 
1024  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kConstantFromPrototype)),
1025  &return_true);
1026 
1027  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNonExistent)), &return_false);
1028 
1029  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNormal)), &normal);
1030 
1031  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kAccessorFromPrototype)),
1032  &return_true);
1033 
1034  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
1035  &return_true);
1036 
1037  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kApiGetter)), &return_true);
1038 
1039  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kSlow)), &slow);
1040 
1041  Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kGlobal)), &global,
1042  &return_lookup);
1043 
1044  BIND(&return_true);
1045  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1046 
1047  BIND(&return_false);
1048  exit_point->Return(FalseConstant());
1049 
1050  BIND(&return_lookup);
1051  {
1052  CSA_DCHECK(this,
1053  Word32Or(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kInterceptor)),
1054  Word32Or(Word32Equal(handler_kind, LOAD_KIND(kProxy)),
1055  Word32Equal(handler_kind,
1056  LOAD_KIND(kModuleExport)))));
1057  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kHasProperty, p->context(),
1058  p->receiver(), p->name());
1059  }
1060 
1061  BIND(&normal);
1062  {
1063  Comment("has_normal");
1064  TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
1065  CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(holder)));
1066  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
1067  Label found(this);
1068  NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
1069  &found, &var_name_index, miss);
1070 
1071  BIND(&found);
1072  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1073  }
1074 
1075  BIND(&global);
1076  {
1077  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsPropertyCell(CAST(holder)));
1078  // Ensure the property cell doesn't contain the hole.
1079  TNode<Object> value =
1080  LoadObjectField(CAST(holder), PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
1081  GotoIf(IsPropertyCellHole(value), miss);
1082 
1083  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1084  }
1085 
1086  BIND(&slow);
1087  {
1088  Comment("load_slow");
1089  if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
1090  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadGlobalIC_Slow, p->context(),
1091  p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
1092  } else {
1093  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kHasProperty, p->context(),
1094  p->receiver(), p->name());
1095  }
1096  }
1097 }
1098 
1099 // Performs actions common to both load and store handlers:
1100 // 1. Checks prototype validity cell.
1101 // 2. If |on_code_handler| is provided, then it checks if the sub handler is
1102 // a smi or code and if it's a code then it calls |on_code_handler| to
1103 // generate a code that handles Code handlers.
1104 // If |on_code_handler| is not provided, then only smi sub handler are
1105 // expected.
1106 // 3. Does access check on lookup start object if
1107 // ICHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits bit is set in the smi
1108 // handler.
1109 // 4. Does dictionary lookup on receiver if
1110 // ICHandler::LookupOnLookupStartObjectBits bit is set in the smi handler. If
1111 // |on_found_on_lookup_start_object| is provided then it calls it to
1112 // generate a code that handles the "found on receiver case" or just misses
1113 // if the |on_found_on_lookup_start_object| is not provided.
1114 // 5. Falls through in a case of a smi handler which is returned from this
1115 // function (tagged!).
1116 // TODO(ishell): Remove templatezation once we move common bits from
1117 // Load/StoreHandler to the base class.
1118 template <typename ICHandler, typename ICParameters>
1119 TNode<Object> AccessorAssembler::HandleProtoHandler(
1120  const ICParameters* p, TNode<DataHandler> handler,
1121  const OnCodeHandler& on_code_handler,
1122  const OnFoundOnLookupStartObject& on_found_on_lookup_start_object,
1123  Label* miss, ICMode ic_mode) {
1124  //
1125  // Check prototype validity cell.
1126  //
1127  {
1128  TNode<Object> maybe_validity_cell =
1129  LoadObjectField(handler, offsetof(ICHandler, validity_cell_));
1130  CheckPrototypeValidityCell(maybe_validity_cell, miss);
1131  }
1132 
1133  //
1134  // Check smi handler bits.
1135  //
1136  {
1137  TNode<Object> smi_or_code_handler =
1138  LoadObjectField(handler, offsetof(ICHandler, smi_handler_));
1139  if (on_code_handler) {
1140  Label if_smi_handler(this);
1141  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(smi_or_code_handler), &if_smi_handler);
1142  TNode<Code> code = CAST(smi_or_code_handler);
1143  on_code_handler(code);
1144 
1145  BIND(&if_smi_handler);
1146  }
1147  TNode<IntPtrT> handler_flags = SmiUntag(CAST(smi_or_code_handler));
1148 
1149  // Lookup on receiver and access checks are not necessary for global ICs
1150  // because in the former case the validity cell check guards modifications
1151  // of the global object and the latter is not applicable to the global
1152  // object.
1153  int mask = ICHandler::LookupOnLookupStartObjectBits::kMask |
1154  ICHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits::kMask;
1155  if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
1156  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsClearWord(handler_flags, mask));
1157  } else {
1158  DCHECK_EQ(ICMode::kNonGlobalIC, ic_mode);
1159 
1160  Label done(this), if_do_access_check(this),
1161  if_lookup_on_lookup_start_object(this);
1162  GotoIf(IsClearWord(handler_flags, mask), &done);
1163  // Only one of the bits can be set at a time.
1164  CSA_DCHECK(this,
1165  WordNotEqual(WordAnd(handler_flags, IntPtrConstant(mask)),
1166  IntPtrConstant(mask)));
1167  Branch(
1168  IsSetWord<typename ICHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits>(
1169  handler_flags),
1170  &if_do_access_check, &if_lookup_on_lookup_start_object);
1171 
1172  BIND(&if_do_access_check);
1173  {
1174  TNode<MaybeObject> data2 = LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 2);
1175  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(data2));
1176  TNode<Context> expected_native_context =
1177  CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(data2, miss));
1178  EmitAccessCheck(expected_native_context, p->context(),
1179  p->lookup_start_object(), &done, miss);
1180  }
1181 
1182  BIND(&if_lookup_on_lookup_start_object);
1183  {
1184  // Dictionary lookup on lookup start object is not necessary for
1185  // Load/StoreGlobalIC (which is the only case when the
1186  // lookup_start_object can be a JSGlobalObject) because prototype
1187  // validity cell check already guards modifications of the global
1188  // object.
1189  CSA_DCHECK(this,
1190  Word32BinaryNot(HasInstanceType(
1191  CAST(p->lookup_start_object()), JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE)));
1192 
1193  TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
1194  CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(p->lookup_start_object())));
1195  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
1196  Label found(this, &var_name_index);
1197  NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(
1198  properties, CAST(p->name()), &found, &var_name_index, &done);
1199  BIND(&found);
1200  {
1201  if (on_found_on_lookup_start_object) {
1202  on_found_on_lookup_start_object(properties, var_name_index.value());
1203  } else {
1204  Goto(miss);
1205  }
1206  }
1207  }
1208 
1209  BIND(&done);
1210  }
1211  return smi_or_code_handler;
1212  }
1213 }
1214 
1215 void AccessorAssembler::HandleLoadICProtoHandler(
1216  const LazyLoadICParameters* p, TNode<DataHandler> handler,
1217  TVariable<Object>* var_holder, TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_smi_handler,
1218  Label* if_smi_handler, Label* miss, ExitPoint* exit_point, ICMode ic_mode,
1219  LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
1220  TNode<Smi> smi_handler = CAST(HandleProtoHandler<LoadHandler>(
1221  p, handler,
1222  // Code sub-handlers are not expected in LoadICs, so no |on_code_handler|.
1223  nullptr,
1224  // on_found_on_lookup_start_object
1225  [=, this](TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties,
1226  TNode<IntPtrT> name_index) {
1227  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
1228  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1229  } else {
1230  TVARIABLE(Uint32T, var_details);
1231  TVARIABLE(Object, var_value);
1232  LoadPropertyFromDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(
1233  properties, name_index, &var_details, &var_value);
1234  TNode<Object> value = CallGetterIfAccessor(
1235  var_value.value(), CAST(var_holder->value()), var_details.value(),
1236  p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), miss);
1237  exit_point->Return(value);
1238  }
1239  },
1240  miss, ic_mode));
1241 
1242  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_holder_or_constant =
1243  LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 1);
1244 
1245  Label load_from_cached_holder(this), is_smi(this), done(this);
1246 
1247  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_holder_or_constant), &is_smi);
1248  Branch(TaggedEqual(maybe_holder_or_constant, NullConstant()), &done,
1249  &load_from_cached_holder);
1250 
1251  BIND(&is_smi);
1252  {
1253  // If the "maybe_holder_or_constant" in the handler is a smi, then it's
1254  // guaranteed that it's not a holder object, but a constant value.
1255  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<LoadHandler::KindBits>(
1256  SmiToInt32(smi_handler)),
1257  LOAD_KIND(kConstantFromPrototype)));
1258  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
1259  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
1260  } else {
1261  exit_point->Return(CAST(maybe_holder_or_constant));
1262  }
1263  }
1264 
1265  BIND(&load_from_cached_holder);
1266  {
1267  // For regular holders, having passed the receiver map check and
1268  // the validity cell check implies that |holder| is
1269  // alive. However, for global object receivers, |maybe_holder| may
1270  // be cleared.
1271  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_holder_or_constant));
1272  TNode<HeapObject> holder =
1273  GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_holder_or_constant, miss);
1274  *var_holder = holder;
1275  Goto(&done);
1276  }
1277 
1278  BIND(&done);
1279  {
1280  *var_smi_handler = smi_handler;
1281  Goto(if_smi_handler);
1282  }
1283 }
1284 
1285 void AccessorAssembler::EmitAccessCheck(TNode<Context> expected_native_context,
1286  TNode<Context> context,
1287  TNode<Object> receiver,
1288  Label* can_access, Label* miss) {
1289  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNativeContext(expected_native_context));
1290 
1291  TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
1292  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(expected_native_context, native_context), can_access);
1293  // If the receiver is not a JSGlobalProxy then we miss.
1294  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(receiver), miss);
1295  GotoIfNot(IsJSGlobalProxy(CAST(receiver)), miss);
1296  // For JSGlobalProxy receiver try to compare security tokens of current
1297  // and expected native contexts.
1298  TNode<Object> expected_token = LoadContextElementNoCell(
1299  expected_native_context, Context::SECURITY_TOKEN_INDEX);
1300  TNode<Object> current_token =
1301  LoadContextElementNoCell(native_context, Context::SECURITY_TOKEN_INDEX);
1302  Branch(TaggedEqual(expected_token, current_token), can_access, miss);
1303 }
1304 
1305 void AccessorAssembler::JumpIfDataProperty(TNode<Uint32T> details,
1306  Label* writable, Label* readonly) {
1307  if (readonly) {
1308  // Accessor properties never have the READ_ONLY attribute set.
1309  GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask),
1310  readonly);
1311  } else {
1312  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNotSetWord32(details,
1313  PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask));
1314  }
1315  TNode<Uint32T> kind = DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::KindField>(details);
1316  GotoIf(
1317  Word32Equal(kind, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData))),
1318  writable);
1319  // Fall through if it's an accessor property.
1320 }
1321 
1322 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICNativeDataProperty(
1323  const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<HeapObject> holder,
1324  TNode<Word32T> handler_word) {
1325  Comment("native_data_property_store");
1326  TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor =
1327  Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
1328  TNode<AccessorInfo> accessor_info =
1329  CAST(LoadDescriptorValue(LoadMap(holder), descriptor));
1330 
1331  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreCallbackProperty, p->context(), p->receiver(),
1332  holder, accessor_info, p->name(), p->value());
1333 }
1334 
1335 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICSmiHandlerJSSharedStructFieldCase(
1336  TNode<Context> context, TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder,
1337  TNode<Object> value) {
1338  CSA_DCHECK(this,
1339  Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word),
1340  STORE_KIND(kSharedStructField)));
1341  CSA_DCHECK(
1342  this,
1343  Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::RepresentationBits>(handler_word),
1344  Int32Constant(Representation::kTagged)));
1345 
1346  TVARIABLE(Object, shared_value, value);
1347  SharedValueBarrier(context, &shared_value);
1348 
1349  TNode<BoolT> is_inobject =
1350  IsSetWord32<StoreHandler::IsInobjectBits>(handler_word);
1351  TNode<HeapObject> property_storage = Select<HeapObject>(
1352  is_inobject, [&]() { return holder; },
1353  [&]() { return LoadFastProperties(holder, true); });
1354 
1355  TNode<UintPtrT> index =
1356  DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::FieldIndexBits>(handler_word);
1357  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(index));
1358 
1359  StoreSharedObjectField(property_storage, offset, shared_value.value());
1360 
1361  // Return the original value.
1362  Return(value);
1363 }
1364 
1365 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICHandlerCase(
1366  const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<MaybeObject> handler, Label* miss,
1367  ICMode ic_mode, ElementSupport support_elements) {
1368  Label if_smi_handler(this), if_nonsmi_handler(this);
1369  Label if_proto_handler(this), call_handler(this),
1370  store_transition_or_global_or_accessor(this);
1371 
1372  Branch(TaggedIsSmi(handler), &if_smi_handler, &if_nonsmi_handler);
1373 
1374  Label if_slow(this), if_generic(this);
1375 
1376  // |handler| is a Smi, encoding what to do. See SmiHandler methods
1377  // for the encoding format.
1378  BIND(&if_smi_handler);
1379  {
1380  TNode<Object> holder = p->receiver();
1381  TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(CAST(handler));
1382 
1383  Label if_fast_smi(this), if_proxy(this), if_interceptor(this);
1384 
1385 #define ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(a, b) \
1386  static_assert(static_cast<intptr_t>(StoreHandler::Kind::a) + 1 == \
1387  static_cast<intptr_t>(StoreHandler::Kind::b));
1388  ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kGlobalProxy, kNormal)
1389  ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kNormal, kInterceptor)
1390  ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kInterceptor, kSlow)
1391  ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kSlow, kProxy)
1392  ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kProxy, kGeneric)
1393  ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE(kGeneric, kKindsNumber)
1394 #undef ASSERT_CONSECUTIVE
1395 
1396  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
1397  DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
1398  GotoIf(Int32LessThan(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kGlobalProxy)), &if_fast_smi);
1399  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kProxy)), &if_proxy);
1400  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kInterceptor)),
1401  &if_interceptor);
1402  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSlow)), &if_slow);
1403  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kGeneric)), &if_generic);
1404  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNormal)));
1405  TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
1406  CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(holder)));
1407 
1408  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
1409  Label dictionary_found(this, &var_name_index);
1410  if (p->IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
1411  NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
1412  &if_slow, nullptr, miss);
1413  } else {
1414  NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, CAST(p->name()),
1415  &dictionary_found,
1416  &var_name_index, miss);
1417  }
1418 
1419  // When dealing with class fields defined with DefineKeyedOwnIC or
1420  // DefineNamedOwnIC, use the slow path to check the existing property.
1421  if (!p->IsAnyDefineOwn()) {
1422  BIND(&dictionary_found);
1423  {
1424  Label if_constant(this), done(this);
1425  TNode<Uint32T> details =
1426  LoadDetailsByKeyIndex(properties, var_name_index.value());
1427  // Check that the property is a writable data property (no accessor).
1428  const int kTypeAndReadOnlyMask =
1429  PropertyDetails::KindField::kMask |
1430  PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask;
1431  static_assert(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData) == 0);
1432  GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, kTypeAndReadOnlyMask), miss);
1433 
1434  if (V8_DICT_PROPERTY_CONST_TRACKING_BOOL) {
1435  GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), miss);
1436  }
1437 
1438  StoreValueByKeyIndex<PropertyDictionary>(
1439  properties, var_name_index.value(), p->value());
1440  Return(p->value());
1441  }
1442  }
1443  BIND(&if_fast_smi);
1444  {
1445  Label data(this), shared_struct_field(this), native_data_property(this);
1446  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
1447  &native_data_property);
1448  Branch(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSharedStructField)),
1449  &shared_struct_field, &data);
1450 
1451  BIND(&native_data_property);
1452  HandleStoreICNativeDataProperty(p, CAST(holder), handler_word);
1453 
1454  BIND(&shared_struct_field);
1455  HandleStoreICSmiHandlerJSSharedStructFieldCase(p->context(), handler_word,
1456  CAST(holder), p->value());
1457 
1458  BIND(&data);
1459  // Handle non-transitioning field stores.
1460  HandleStoreICSmiHandlerCase(handler_word, CAST(holder), p->value(), miss);
1461  }
1462 
1463  BIND(&if_proxy);
1464  {
1465  CSA_DCHECK(this, BoolConstant(!p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()));
1466  HandleStoreToProxy(p, CAST(holder), miss, support_elements);
1467  }
1468 
1469  BIND(&if_interceptor);
1470  {
1471  Comment("store_interceptor");
1472  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStorePropertyWithInterceptor, p->context(),
1473  p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
1474  }
1475 
1476  BIND(&if_slow);
1477  {
1478  Comment("store_slow");
1479  // The slow case calls into the runtime to complete the store without
1480  // causing an IC miss that would otherwise cause a transition to the
1481  // generic stub.
1482  if (ic_mode == ICMode::kGlobalIC) {
1483  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreGlobalIC_Slow, p->context(), p->value(),
1484  p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(), p->name());
1485  } else {
1486  Runtime::FunctionId id;
1487  if (p->IsDefineNamedOwn()) {
1488  id = Runtime::kDefineNamedOwnIC_Slow;
1489  } else if (p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()) {
1490  id = Runtime::kDefineKeyedOwnIC_Slow;
1491  } else {
1492  id = Runtime::kKeyedStoreIC_Slow;
1493  }
1494  TailCallRuntime(id, p->context(), p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
1495  }
1496  }
1497 
1498  BIND(&if_generic);
1499  {
1500  Comment("store_generic");
1501  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kKeyedStoreIC_Megamorphic, p->context(),
1502  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
1503  p->vector());
1504  }
1505  }
1506 
1507  BIND(&if_nonsmi_handler);
1508  {
1509  TNode<HeapObjectReference> ref_handler = CAST(handler);
1510  GotoIf(IsWeakOrCleared(ref_handler),
1511  &store_transition_or_global_or_accessor);
1512  TNode<HeapObject> strong_handler = CAST(handler);
1513  TNode<Map> handler_map = LoadMap(strong_handler);
1514  Branch(IsCodeMap(handler_map), &call_handler, &if_proto_handler);
1515 
1516  BIND(&if_proto_handler);
1517  {
1518  // Note, although DefineOwnICs don't reqiure checking for prototype
1519  // chain modifications the proto handlers shape is still used for
1520  // StoreHandler::StoreElementTransition in order to store both Code
1521  // handler and transition target map.
1522  HandleStoreICProtoHandler(p, CAST(strong_handler), &if_slow, miss,
1523  ic_mode, support_elements);
1524  }
1525 
1526  // |handler| is a heap object. Must be code, call it.
1527  BIND(&call_handler);
1528  {
1529  TNode<Code> code_handler = CAST(strong_handler);
1530  TailCallStub(StoreWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
1531  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
1532  p->vector());
1533  }
1534  }
1535 
1536  BIND(&store_transition_or_global_or_accessor);
1537  {
1538  // Load value or miss if the {handler} weak cell is cleared.
1539  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(handler));
1540  TNode<HeapObject> strong_handler = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(handler, miss);
1541 
1542  Label store_global(this), store_transition(this), store_accessor(this);
1543  TNode<Map> strong_handler_map = LoadMap(strong_handler);
1544  GotoIf(IsPropertyCellMap(strong_handler_map), &store_global);
1545  Branch(IsAccessorPairMap(strong_handler_map), &store_accessor,
1546  &store_transition);
1547 
1548  BIND(&store_global);
1549  {
1550  if (p->IsDefineNamedOwn()) {
1551  // The global proxy has its attributes set in the global object,
1552  // which can't be handled by StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase when
1553  // defining public fields. Handle it in runtime.
1554  GotoIf(IsJSGlobalProxy(CAST(p->receiver())), &if_slow);
1555  } else if (p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()) {
1556  Label proceed_defining(this);
1557  // StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase doesn't support definition
1558  // of private fields, so handle them in runtime.
1559  GotoIfNot(IsSymbol(CAST(p->name())), &proceed_defining);
1560  Branch(IsPrivateName(CAST(p->name())), &if_slow, &proceed_defining);
1561  BIND(&proceed_defining);
1562  }
1563 
1564  TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell = CAST(strong_handler);
1565  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
1566  StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(property_cell, p->value(), &direct_exit,
1567  miss);
1568  }
1569  BIND(&store_accessor);
1570  {
1571  TNode<AccessorPair> pair = CAST(strong_handler);
1572  TNode<JSFunction> setter = CAST(LoadAccessorPairSetter(pair));
1573  // As long as this code path is not used for StoreSuperIC the receiver
1574  // is known to be neither undefined nor null.
1575  ConvertReceiverMode mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
1576  Return(
1577  CallFunction(p->context(), setter, mode, p->receiver(), p->value()));
1578  }
1579  BIND(&store_transition);
1580  {
1581  TNode<Map> map = CAST(strong_handler);
1582  HandleStoreICTransitionMapHandlerCase(p, map, miss,
1583  p->IsAnyDefineOwn()
1584  ? kDontCheckPrototypeValidity
1585  : kCheckPrototypeValidity);
1586  Return(p->value());
1587  }
1588  }
1589 }
1590 
1591 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICTransitionMapHandlerCase(
1592  const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<Map> transition_map, Label* miss,
1593  StoreTransitionMapFlags flags) {
1594  DCHECK_EQ(0, flags & ~kStoreTransitionMapFlagsMask);
1595  if (flags & kCheckPrototypeValidity) {
1596  TNode<Object> maybe_validity_cell =
1597  LoadObjectField(transition_map, Map::kPrototypeValidityCellOffset);
1598  CheckPrototypeValidityCell(maybe_validity_cell, miss);
1599  }
1600 
1601  TNode<Uint32T> bitfield3 = LoadMapBitField3(transition_map);
1602  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsClearWord32<Map::Bits3::IsDictionaryMapBit>(bitfield3));
1603  GotoIf(IsSetWord32<Map::Bits3::IsDeprecatedBit>(bitfield3), miss);
1604 
1605  // Load last descriptor details.
1606  TNode<UintPtrT> nof =
1607  DecodeWordFromWord32<Map::Bits3::NumberOfOwnDescriptorsBits>(bitfield3);
1608  CSA_DCHECK(this, WordNotEqual(nof, IntPtrConstant(0)));
1609  TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors = LoadMapDescriptors(transition_map);
1610 
1611  TNode<IntPtrT> factor = IntPtrConstant(DescriptorArray::kEntrySize);
1612  TNode<IntPtrT> last_key_index = UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(IntPtrAdd(
1613  IntPtrConstant(DescriptorArray::ToKeyIndex(-1)), IntPtrMul(nof, factor)));
1614  if (flags & kValidateTransitionHandler) {
1615  TNode<Name> key = LoadKeyByKeyIndex(descriptors, last_key_index);
1616  GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(key, p->name()), miss);
1617  } else {
1618  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(LoadKeyByKeyIndex(descriptors, last_key_index),
1619  p->name()));
1620  }
1621  TNode<Uint32T> details = LoadDetailsByKeyIndex(descriptors, last_key_index);
1622  if (flags & kValidateTransitionHandler) {
1623  // Follow transitions only in the following cases:
1624  // 1) name is a non-private symbol and attributes equal to NONE,
1625  // 2) name is a private symbol and attributes equal to DONT_ENUM.
1626  Label attributes_ok(this);
1627  const int kKindAndAttributesDontDeleteReadOnlyMask =
1628  PropertyDetails::KindField::kMask |
1629  PropertyDetails::kAttributesDontDeleteMask |
1630  PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask;
1631  static_assert(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData) == 0);
1632  // Both DontDelete and ReadOnly attributes must not be set and it has to be
1633  // a kData property.
1634  GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, kKindAndAttributesDontDeleteReadOnlyMask),
1635  miss);
1636 
1637  // DontEnum attribute is allowed only for private symbols and vice versa.
1638  Branch(Word32Equal(
1639  IsSetWord32(details, PropertyDetails::kAttributesDontEnumMask),
1640  IsPrivateSymbol(CAST(p->name()))),
1641  &attributes_ok, miss);
1642 
1643  BIND(&attributes_ok);
1644  }
1645 
1646  OverwriteExistingFastDataProperty(CAST(p->receiver()), transition_map,
1647  descriptors, last_key_index, details,
1648  p->value(), miss, true);
1649 }
1650 
1651 void AccessorAssembler::UpdateMayHaveInterestingProperty(
1652  TNode<PropertyDictionary> dict, TNode<Name> name) {
1653  Comment("UpdateMayHaveInterestingProperty");
1654  Label done(this);
1655 
1656  if constexpr (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
1657  // TODO(pthier): Add flags to swiss dictionaries.
1658  Goto(&done);
1659  } else {
1660  GotoIfNot(IsInterestingProperty(name), &done);
1661  TNode<Smi> flags = GetNameDictionaryFlags(dict);
1662  flags = SmiOr(
1663  flags,
1664  SmiConstant(
1665  NameDictionary::MayHaveInterestingPropertiesBit::encode(true)));
1666  SetNameDictionaryFlags(dict, flags);
1667  Goto(&done);
1668  }
1669  BIND(&done);
1670 }
1671 
1672 void AccessorAssembler::CheckFieldType(TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors,
1673  TNode<IntPtrT> name_index,
1674  TNode<Word32T> representation,
1675  TNode<Object> value, Label* bailout) {
1676  Label r_smi(this), r_double(this), r_heapobject(this), all_fine(this);
1677  GotoIf(Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kSmi)),
1678  &r_smi);
1679  GotoIf(Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1680  &r_double);
1681  GotoIf(
1682  Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kHeapObject)),
1683  &r_heapobject);
1684  GotoIf(Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kNone)),
1685  bailout);
1686  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(representation,
1687  Int32Constant(Representation::kTagged)));
1688  Goto(&all_fine);
1689 
1690  BIND(&r_smi);
1691  { Branch(TaggedIsSmi(value), &all_fine, bailout); }
1692 
1693  BIND(&r_double);
1694  {
1695  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), &all_fine);
1696  Branch(IsHeapNumber(CAST(value)), &all_fine, bailout);
1697  }
1698 
1699  BIND(&r_heapobject);
1700  {
1701  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), bailout);
1702  TNode<MaybeObject> field_type =
1703  LoadFieldTypeByKeyIndex(descriptors, name_index);
1704  const Address kAnyType = FieldType::Any().ptr();
1705  // FieldType::Any can hold any value.
1706  GotoIf(
1707  TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(kAnyType))),
1708  &all_fine);
1709  // FieldType::Class(...) performs a map check.
1710  // If the type is None we want this check to fail too, thus we compare the
1711  // maybe weak field type as is against a weak map ptr.
1712 #ifdef DEBUG
1713  {
1714  // Check the field type is None or a weak map.
1715  Label check_done(this);
1716  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(
1717  FieldType::None().ptr()))),
1718  &check_done);
1719  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(field_type)));
1720  Goto(&check_done);
1721  BIND(&check_done);
1722  }
1723 #endif // DEBUG
1724  Branch(TaggedEqual(MakeWeak(LoadMap(CAST(value))), field_type), &all_fine,
1725  bailout);
1726  }
1727 
1728  BIND(&all_fine);
1729 }
1730 
1731 TNode<BoolT> AccessorAssembler::IsPropertyDetailsConst(TNode<Uint32T> details) {
1732  return Word32Equal(
1733  DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::ConstnessField>(details),
1734  Int32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(PropertyConstness::kConst)));
1735 }
1736 
1737 void AccessorAssembler::OverwriteExistingFastDataProperty(
1738  TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Map> object_map,
1739  TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors, TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_name_index,
1740  TNode<Uint32T> details, TNode<Object> value, Label* slow,
1741  bool do_transitioning_store) {
1742  Label done(this), if_field(this), if_descriptor(this);
1743 
1744  CSA_DCHECK(this,
1745  Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::KindField>(details),
1746  Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData))));
1747 
1748  Branch(Word32Equal(
1749  DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::LocationField>(details),
1750  Int32Constant(static_cast<int32_t>(PropertyLocation::kField))),
1751  &if_field, &if_descriptor);
1752 
1753  BIND(&if_field);
1754  {
1755  TNode<Uint32T> representation =
1756  DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::RepresentationField>(details);
1757 
1758  CheckFieldType(descriptors, descriptor_name_index, representation, value,
1759  slow);
1760 
1761  TNode<UintPtrT> field_index =
1762  DecodeWordFromWord32<PropertyDetails::FieldIndexField>(details);
1763  field_index = Unsigned(
1764  IntPtrAdd(field_index,
1765  Unsigned(LoadMapInobjectPropertiesStartInWords(object_map))));
1766  TNode<IntPtrT> instance_size_in_words =
1767  LoadMapInstanceSizeInWords(object_map);
1768 
1769  Label inobject(this), backing_store(this);
1770  Branch(UintPtrLessThan(field_index, instance_size_in_words), &inobject,
1771  &backing_store);
1772 
1773  BIND(&inobject);
1774  {
1775  TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(field_index));
1776  Label tagged_rep(this), double_rep(this);
1777  Branch(
1778  Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1779  &double_rep, &tagged_rep);
1780  BIND(&double_rep);
1781  {
1782  TNode<Float64T> double_value = ChangeNumberToFloat64(CAST(value));
1783  if (do_transitioning_store) {
1784  TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1785  AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(double_value);
1786  StoreMap(object, object_map);
1787  StoreObjectField(object, field_offset, heap_number);
1788  } else {
1789  GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1790  TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1791  CAST(LoadObjectField(object, field_offset));
1792  StoreHeapNumberValue(heap_number, double_value);
1793  }
1794  Goto(&done);
1795  }
1796 
1797  BIND(&tagged_rep);
1798  {
1799  if (do_transitioning_store) {
1800  StoreMap(object, object_map);
1801  } else {
1802  GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1803  }
1804  StoreObjectField(object, field_offset, value);
1805  Goto(&done);
1806  }
1807  }
1808 
1809  BIND(&backing_store);
1810  {
1811  TNode<IntPtrT> backing_store_index =
1812  Signed(IntPtrSub(field_index, instance_size_in_words));
1813 
1814  if (do_transitioning_store) {
1815  // Allocate mutable heap number before extending properties backing
1816  // store to ensure that heap verifier will not see the heap in
1817  // inconsistent state.
1818  TVARIABLE(Object, var_value, value);
1819  {
1820  Label cont(this);
1821  GotoIf(Word32NotEqual(representation,
1822  Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1823  &cont);
1824  {
1825  TNode<Float64T> double_value = ChangeNumberToFloat64(CAST(value));
1826  TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1827  AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(double_value);
1828  var_value = heap_number;
1829  Goto(&cont);
1830  }
1831  BIND(&cont);
1832  }
1833 
1834  TNode<PropertyArray> properties =
1835  ExtendPropertiesBackingStore(object, backing_store_index);
1836  StorePropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index,
1837  var_value.value());
1838  StoreMap(object, object_map);
1839  Goto(&done);
1840 
1841  } else {
1842  Label tagged_rep(this), double_rep(this);
1843  TNode<PropertyArray> properties =
1844  CAST(LoadFastProperties(CAST(object), true));
1845  Branch(
1846  Word32Equal(representation, Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)),
1847  &double_rep, &tagged_rep);
1848  BIND(&double_rep);
1849  {
1850  GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1851  TNode<HeapNumber> heap_number =
1852  CAST(LoadPropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index));
1853  TNode<Float64T> double_value = ChangeNumberToFloat64(CAST(value));
1854  StoreHeapNumberValue(heap_number, double_value);
1855  Goto(&done);
1856  }
1857  BIND(&tagged_rep);
1858  {
1859  GotoIf(IsPropertyDetailsConst(details), slow);
1860  StorePropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index, value);
1861  Goto(&done);
1862  }
1863  }
1864  }
1865  }
1866 
1867  BIND(&if_descriptor);
1868  {
1869  // Check that constant matches value.
1870  TNode<Object> constant =
1871  LoadValueByKeyIndex(descriptors, descriptor_name_index);
1872  GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(value, constant), slow);
1873 
1874  if (do_transitioning_store) {
1875  StoreMap(object, object_map);
1876  }
1877  Goto(&done);
1878  }
1879  BIND(&done);
1880 }
1881 
1882 void AccessorAssembler::StoreJSSharedStructField(
1883  TNode<Context> context, TNode<HeapObject> shared_struct,
1884  TNode<Map> shared_struct_map, TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors,
1885  TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_name_index, TNode<Uint32T> details,
1886  TNode<Object> maybe_local_value) {
1887  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsJSSharedStruct(shared_struct));
1888 
1889  Label done(this);
1890 
1891  TNode<UintPtrT> field_index =
1892  DecodeWordFromWord32<PropertyDetails::FieldIndexField>(details);
1893  field_index = Unsigned(IntPtrAdd(
1894  field_index,
1895  Unsigned(LoadMapInobjectPropertiesStartInWords(shared_struct_map))));
1896 
1897  TNode<IntPtrT> instance_size_in_words =
1898  LoadMapInstanceSizeInWords(shared_struct_map);
1899 
1900  TVARIABLE(Object, shared_value, maybe_local_value);
1901  SharedValueBarrier(context, &shared_value);
1902 
1903  Label inobject(this), backing_store(this);
1904  Branch(UintPtrLessThan(field_index, instance_size_in_words), &inobject,
1905  &backing_store);
1906 
1907  BIND(&inobject);
1908  {
1909  TNode<IntPtrT> field_offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(field_index));
1910  StoreSharedObjectField(shared_struct, field_offset, shared_value.value());
1911  Goto(&done);
1912  }
1913 
1914  BIND(&backing_store);
1915  {
1916  TNode<IntPtrT> backing_store_index =
1917  Signed(IntPtrSub(field_index, instance_size_in_words));
1918 
1919  CSA_DCHECK(
1920  this,
1921  Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::RepresentationField>(details),
1922  Int32Constant(Representation::kTagged)));
1923  TNode<PropertyArray> properties =
1924  CAST(LoadFastProperties(CAST(shared_struct), true));
1925  StoreJSSharedStructPropertyArrayElement(properties, backing_store_index,
1926  shared_value.value());
1927  Goto(&done);
1928  }
1929 
1930  BIND(&done);
1931 }
