1933 void AccessorAssembler::CheckPrototypeValidityCell(
1934  TNode<Object> maybe_validity_cell, Label* miss) {
1935  Label done(this);
1936  GotoIf(
1937  TaggedEqual(maybe_validity_cell, SmiConstant(Map::kPrototypeChainValid)),
1938  &done);
1939  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(maybe_validity_cell));
1940 
1941  TNode<Object> cell_value =
1942  LoadObjectField(CAST(maybe_validity_cell), Cell::kValueOffset);
1943  Branch(TaggedEqual(cell_value, SmiConstant(Map::kPrototypeChainValid)), &done,
1944  miss);
1945 
1946  BIND(&done);
1947 }
1948 
1949 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICProtoHandler(
1950  const StoreICParameters* p, TNode<StoreHandler> handler, Label* slow,
1951  Label* miss, ICMode ic_mode, ElementSupport support_elements) {
1952  Comment("HandleStoreICProtoHandler");
1953 
1954  OnCodeHandler on_code_handler;
1955  if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
1956  // Code sub-handlers are expected only in KeyedStoreICs.
1957  on_code_handler = [=, this](TNode<Code> code_handler) {
1958  // This is either element store or transitioning element store.
1959  Label if_element_store(this), if_transitioning_element_store(this);
1960  Branch(IsStoreHandler0Map(LoadMap(handler)), &if_element_store,
1961  &if_transitioning_element_store);
1962  BIND(&if_element_store);
1963  {
1964  TailCallStub(StoreWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
1965  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
1966  p->vector());
1967  }
1968 
1969  BIND(&if_transitioning_element_store);
1970  {
1971  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_transition_map =
1972  LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 1);
1973  TNode<Map> transition_map =
1974  CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_transition_map, miss));
1975 
1976  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(transition_map), miss);
1977 
1978  TailCallStub(StoreTransitionDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
1979  p->receiver(), p->name(), transition_map, p->value(),
1980  p->slot(), p->vector());
1981  }
1982  };
1983  }
1984 
1985  TNode<Object> smi_handler = HandleProtoHandler<StoreHandler>(
1986  p, handler, on_code_handler,
1987  // on_found_on_lookup_start_object
1988  [=, this](TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties,
1989  TNode<IntPtrT> name_index) {
1990  TNode<Uint32T> details = LoadDetailsByKeyIndex(properties, name_index);
1991  // Check that the property is a writable data property (no accessor).
1992  const int kTypeAndReadOnlyMask =
1993  PropertyDetails::KindField::kMask |
1994  PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask;
1995  static_assert(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData) == 0);
1996  GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, kTypeAndReadOnlyMask), miss);
1997 
1998  StoreValueByKeyIndex<PropertyDictionary>(properties, name_index,
1999  p->value());
2000  Return(p->value());
2001  },
2002  miss, ic_mode);
2003 
2004  {
2005  Label if_add_normal(this), if_store_global_proxy(this), if_api_setter(this),
2006  if_accessor(this), if_native_data_property(this);
2007 
2008  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsSmi(smi_handler));
2009  TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(CAST(smi_handler));
2010 
2011  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
2012  DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
2013  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNormal)), &if_add_normal);
2014 
2015  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSlow)), slow);
2016 
2017  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_holder = LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 1);
2018  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_holder));
2019  TNode<HeapObject> holder = GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_holder, miss);
2020 
2021  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kGlobalProxy)),
2022  &if_store_global_proxy);
2023 
2024  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kAccessorFromPrototype)),
2025  &if_accessor);
2026 
2027  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kNativeDataProperty)),
2028  &if_native_data_property);
2029 
2030  GotoIf(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kApiSetter)), &if_api_setter);
2031 
2032  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kProxy)));
2033  HandleStoreToProxy(p, CAST(holder), miss, support_elements);
2034 
2035  BIND(&if_add_normal);
2036  {
2037  // This is a case of "transitioning store" to a dictionary mode object
2038  // when the property does not exist. The "existing property" case is
2039  // covered above by LookupOnLookupStartObject bit handling of the smi
2040  // handler.
2041  Label slow_runtime_call(this);
2042  TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadMap(CAST(p->receiver()));
2043  InvalidateValidityCellIfPrototype(receiver_map);
2044 
2045  TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
2046  CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(p->receiver())));
2047  TNode<Name> name = CAST(p->name());
2048  AddToDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(properties, name, p->value(),
2049  &slow_runtime_call);
2050  UpdateMayHaveInterestingProperty(properties, name);
2051  Return(p->value());
2052 
2053  BIND(&slow_runtime_call);
2054  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kAddDictionaryProperty, p->context(),
2055  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value());
2056  }
2057 
2058  BIND(&if_accessor);
2059  {
2060  Comment("accessor_store");
2061  // The "holder" slot (data1) in the from-prototype StoreHandler is
2062  // instead directly the setter function.
2063  TNode<JSFunction> setter = CAST(holder);
2064 
2065  // As long as this code path is not used for StoreSuperIC the receiver
2066  // is known to be neither undefined nor null.
2067  ConvertReceiverMode mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
2068  Return(
2069  CallFunction(p->context(), setter, mode, p->receiver(), p->value()));
2070  }
2071 
2072  BIND(&if_native_data_property);
2073  HandleStoreICNativeDataProperty(p, holder, handler_word);
2074 
2075  BIND(&if_api_setter);
2076  {
2077  Comment("api_setter");
2078  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(handler));
2079  TNode<FunctionTemplateInfo> function_template_info = CAST(holder);
2080 
2081  // Context is stored either in data2 or data3 field depending on whether
2082  // the access check is enabled for this handler or not.
2083  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_context = Select<MaybeObject>(
2084  IsSetWord32<StoreHandler::DoAccessCheckOnLookupStartObjectBits>(
2085  handler_word),
2086  [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 3); },
2087  [=, this] { return LoadHandlerDataField(handler, 2); });
2088 
2089  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_context));
2090  TNode<Object> context = Select<Object>(
2091  IsCleared(maybe_context), [=, this] { return SmiConstant(0); },
2092  [=, this] { return GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_context); });
2093 
2094  TNode<Int32T> argc = Int32Constant(1);
2095  TNode<Context> caller_context = p->context();
2096  Return(CallBuiltin(Builtin::kCallApiCallbackGeneric, context, argc,
2097  caller_context, function_template_info, p->receiver(),
2098  p->value()));
2099  }
2100 
2101  BIND(&if_store_global_proxy);
2102  {
2103  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
2104  // StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase doesn't properly handle private names
2105  // but they are not expected here anyway.
2106  CSA_DCHECK(this, BoolConstant(!p->IsDefineKeyedOwn()));
2107  StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(CAST(holder), p->value(), &direct_exit,
2108  miss);
2109  }
2110  }
2111 }
2112 
2113 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreToProxy(const StoreICParameters* p,
2114  TNode<JSProxy> proxy, Label* miss,
2115  ElementSupport support_elements) {
2116  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
2117  TVARIABLE(Name, var_unique);
2118 
2119  Label if_index(this), if_unique_name(this),
2120  to_name_failed(this, Label::kDeferred);
2121 
2122  if (support_elements == kSupportElements) {
2123  TryToName(p->name(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name, &var_unique,
2124  &to_name_failed);
2125 
2126  BIND(&if_unique_name);
2127  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxySetProperty, p->context(), proxy,
2128  var_unique.value(), p->value(), p->receiver());
2129  Return(p->value());
2130 
2131  // The index case is handled earlier by the runtime.
2132  BIND(&if_index);
2133  // TODO(mslekova): introduce TryToName that doesn't try to compute
2134  // the intptr index value
2135  Goto(&to_name_failed);
2136 
2137  BIND(&to_name_failed);
2138  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kSetPropertyWithReceiver, p->context(), proxy,
2139  p->name(), p->value(), p->receiver());
2140  } else {
2141  TNode<Object> name = CallBuiltin(Builtin::kToName, p->context(), p->name());
2142  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxySetProperty, p->context(), proxy, name,
2143  p->value(), p->receiver());
2144  }
2145 }
2146 
2147 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreICSmiHandlerCase(TNode<Word32T> handler_word,
2148  TNode<JSObject> holder,
2149  TNode<Object> value,
2150  Label* miss) {
2151  Comment("field store");
2152 #ifdef DEBUG
2153  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
2154  DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
2155  CSA_DCHECK(this,
2156  Word32Or(Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kField)),
2157  Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kConstField))));
2158 #endif
2159 
2160  TNode<Uint32T> field_representation =
2161  DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::RepresentationBits>(handler_word);
2162 
2163  Label if_smi_field(this), if_double_field(this), if_heap_object_field(this),
2164  if_tagged_field(this);
2165 
2166  int32_t case_values[] = {Representation::kTagged, Representation::kHeapObject,
2167  Representation::kSmi};
2168  Label* case_labels[] = {&if_tagged_field, &if_heap_object_field,
2169  &if_smi_field};
2170 
2171  Switch(field_representation, &if_double_field, case_values, case_labels, 3);
2172 
2173  BIND(&if_tagged_field);
2174  {
2175  Comment("store tagged field");
2176  HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, std::nullopt,
2177  Representation::Tagged(), miss);
2178  }
2179 
2180  BIND(&if_heap_object_field);
2181  {
2182  Comment("heap object field checks");
2183  CheckHeapObjectTypeMatchesDescriptor(handler_word, holder, value, miss);
2184 
2185  Comment("store heap object field");
2186  HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, std::nullopt,
2187  Representation::HeapObject(), miss);
2188  }
2189 
2190  BIND(&if_smi_field);
2191  {
2192  Comment("smi field checks");
2193  GotoIfNot(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
2194 
2195  Comment("store smi field");
2196  HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, std::nullopt,
2197  Representation::Smi(), miss);
2198  }
2199 
2200  BIND(&if_double_field);
2201  {
2202  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(field_representation,
2203  Int32Constant(Representation::kDouble)));
2204  Comment("double field checks");
2205  TNode<Float64T> double_value = TryTaggedToFloat64(value,
2206 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2207  nullptr,
2208 #endif // V8_ENABLE_EXPERIMENTAL_UNDEFINED_DOUBLE
2209  miss);
2210  CheckDescriptorConsidersNumbersMutable(handler_word, holder, miss);
2211 
2212  Comment("store double field");
2213  HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(handler_word, holder, value, double_value,
2214  Representation::Double(), miss);
2215  }
2216 }
2217 
2218 void AccessorAssembler::CheckHeapObjectTypeMatchesDescriptor(
2219  TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder, TNode<Object> value,
2220  Label* bailout) {
2221  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), bailout);
2222 
2223  Label done(this);
2224  // Skip field type check in favor of constant value check when storing
2225  // to constant field.
2226  GotoIf(Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word),
2227  STORE_KIND(kConstField)),
2228  &done);
2229  TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor =
2230  Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
2231  TNode<MaybeObject> field_type =
2232  LoadDescriptorValueOrFieldType(LoadMap(holder), descriptor);
2233 
2234  const Address kAnyType = FieldType::Any().ptr();
2235  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(kAnyType))),
2236  &done);
2237  // Check that value type matches the field type.
2238  {
2239  // If the type is None we want this check to fail too, thus we compare the
2240  // maybe weak field type as is against a weak map ptr.
2241 #ifdef DEBUG
2242  {
2243  // Check the field type is None or a weak map.
2244  Label check_done(this);
2245  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(field_type, BitcastWordToTagged(IntPtrConstant(
2246  FieldType::None().ptr()))),
2247  &check_done);
2248  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsMap(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(field_type)));
2249  Goto(&check_done);
2250  BIND(&check_done);
2251  }
2252 #endif // DEBUG
2253  Branch(TaggedEqual(MakeWeak(LoadMap(CAST(value))), field_type), &done,
2254  bailout);
2255  }
2256  BIND(&done);
2257 }
2258 
2259 void AccessorAssembler::CheckDescriptorConsidersNumbersMutable(
2260  TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder, Label* bailout) {
2261  // We have to check that the representation is Double. Checking the value
2262  // (either in the field or being assigned) is not enough, as we could have
2263  // transitioned to Tagged but still be holding a HeapNumber, which would no
2264  // longer be allowed to be mutable.
2265 
2266  // TODO(leszeks): We could skip the representation check in favor of a
2267  // constant value check in HandleStoreFieldAndReturn here, but then
2268  // HandleStoreFieldAndReturn would need an IsHeapNumber check in case both the
2269  // representation changed and the value is no longer a HeapNumber.
2270  TNode<IntPtrT> descriptor_entry =
2271  Signed(DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::DescriptorBits>(handler_word));
2272  TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors = LoadMapDescriptors(LoadMap(holder));
2273  TNode<Uint32T> details =
2274  LoadDetailsByDescriptorEntry(descriptors, descriptor_entry);
2275 
2276  GotoIfNot(IsEqualInWord32<PropertyDetails::RepresentationField>(
2277  details, Representation::kDouble),
2278  bailout);
2279 }
2280 
2281 void AccessorAssembler::GotoIfNotSameNumberBitPattern(TNode<Float64T> left,
2282  TNode<Float64T> right,
2283  Label* miss) {
2284  // TODO(verwaest): Use a single compare on 64bit archs.
2285  const TNode<Uint32T> lhs_hi = Float64ExtractHighWord32(left);
2286  const TNode<Uint32T> rhs_hi = Float64ExtractHighWord32(right);
2287  GotoIfNot(Word32Equal(lhs_hi, rhs_hi), miss);
2288  const TNode<Uint32T> lhs_lo = Float64ExtractLowWord32(left);
2289  const TNode<Uint32T> rhs_lo = Float64ExtractLowWord32(right);
2290  GotoIfNot(Word32Equal(lhs_lo, rhs_lo), miss);
2291 }
2292 
2293 void AccessorAssembler::HandleStoreFieldAndReturn(
2294  TNode<Word32T> handler_word, TNode<JSObject> holder, TNode<Object> value,
2295  std::optional<TNode<Float64T>> double_value, Representation representation,
2296  Label* miss) {
2297  bool store_value_as_double = representation.IsDouble();
2298 
2299  TNode<BoolT> is_inobject =
2300  IsSetWord32<StoreHandler::IsInobjectBits>(handler_word);
2301  TNode<HeapObject> property_storage = Select<HeapObject>(
2302  is_inobject, [&]() { return holder; },
2303  [&]() { return LoadFastProperties(holder, true); });
2304 
2305  TNode<UintPtrT> index =
2306  DecodeWordFromWord32<StoreHandler::FieldIndexBits>(handler_word);
2307  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = Signed(TimesTaggedSize(index));
2308 
2309  // For Double fields, we want to mutate the current double-value
2310  // field rather than changing it to point at a new HeapNumber.
2311  if (store_value_as_double) {
2312  TVARIABLE(HeapObject, actual_property_storage, property_storage);
2313  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, actual_offset, offset);
2314 
2315  Label property_and_offset_ready(this);
2316 
2317  // Store the double value directly into the mutable HeapNumber.
2318  TNode<Object> field = LoadObjectField(property_storage, offset);
2319  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsHeapNumber(CAST(field)));
2320  actual_property_storage = CAST(field);
2321  actual_offset = IntPtrConstant(offsetof(HeapNumber, value_));
2322  Goto(&property_and_offset_ready);
2323 
2324  BIND(&property_and_offset_ready);
2325  property_storage = actual_property_storage.value();
2326  offset = actual_offset.value();
2327  }
2328 
2329  // Do constant value check if necessary.
2330  Label do_store(this);
2331  GotoIfNot(Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word),
2332  STORE_KIND(kConstField)),
2333  &do_store);
2334  {
2335  if (store_value_as_double) {
2336  TNode<Float64T> current_value =
2337  LoadObjectField<Float64T>(property_storage, offset);
2338  GotoIfNotSameNumberBitPattern(current_value, *double_value, miss);
2339  Return(value);
2340  } else {
2341  TNode<Object> current_value = LoadObjectField(property_storage, offset);
2342  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(current_value, value), miss);
2343  Return(value);
2344  }
2345  }
2346 
2347  BIND(&do_store);
2348  // Do the store.
2349  if (store_value_as_double) {
2350  StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(property_storage, offset, *double_value);
2351  } else if (representation.IsSmi()) {
2352  TNode<Smi> value_smi = CAST(value);
2353  StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(property_storage, offset, value_smi);
2354  } else {
2355  StoreObjectField(property_storage, offset, value);
2356  }
2357 
2358  Return(value);
2359 }
2360 
2361 TNode<PropertyArray> AccessorAssembler::ExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
2362  TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<IntPtrT> index) {
2363  Comment("[ Extend storage");
2364 
2365  TVARIABLE(HeapObject, var_properties);
2366  TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_encoded_hash);
2367  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_length);
2368 
2369  TNode<Object> properties =
2370  LoadObjectField(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset);
2371 
2372  Label if_smi_hash(this), if_property_array(this), extend_store(this);
2373  Branch(TaggedIsSmi(properties), &if_smi_hash, &if_property_array);
2374 
2375  BIND(&if_smi_hash);
2376  {
2377  TNode<Int32T> hash = SmiToInt32(CAST(properties));
2378  TNode<Int32T> encoded_hash =
2379  Word32Shl(hash, Int32Constant(PropertyArray::HashField::kShift));
2380  var_encoded_hash = encoded_hash;
2381  var_length = IntPtrConstant(0);
2382  var_properties = EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
2383  Goto(&extend_store);
2384  }
2385 
2386  BIND(&if_property_array);
2387  {
2388  var_properties = CAST(properties);
2389  TNode<Int32T> length_and_hash_int32 = LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(
2390  var_properties.value(), PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset);
2391  var_encoded_hash = Word32And(
2392  length_and_hash_int32, Int32Constant(PropertyArray::HashField::kMask));
2393  var_length = ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(
2394  Word32And(length_and_hash_int32,
2395  Int32Constant(PropertyArray::LengthField::kMask)));
2396  Goto(&extend_store);
2397  }
2398 
2399  BIND(&extend_store);
2400  {
2401  TVARIABLE(HeapObject, var_new_properties, var_properties.value());
2402  Label done(this);
2403  // Previous property deletion could have left behind unused backing store
2404  // capacity even for a map that think it doesn't have any unused fields.
2405  // Perform a bounds check to see if we actually have to grow the array.
2406  GotoIf(UintPtrLessThan(index, ParameterToIntPtr(var_length.value())),
2407  &done);
2408 
2409  TNode<IntPtrT> delta = IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kFieldsAdded);
2410  TNode<IntPtrT> new_capacity = IntPtrAdd(var_length.value(), delta);
2411 
2412  // Grow properties array.
2413  DCHECK(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors + JSObject::kFieldsAdded <
2414  FixedArrayBase::GetMaxLengthForNewSpaceAllocation(PACKED_ELEMENTS));
2415  // The size of a new properties backing store is guaranteed to be small
2416  // enough that the new backing store will be allocated in new space.
2417  CSA_DCHECK(this, IntPtrLessThan(new_capacity,
2418  IntPtrConstant(kMaxNumberOfDescriptors +
2419  JSObject::kFieldsAdded)));
2420 
2421  TNode<PropertyArray> new_properties = AllocatePropertyArray(new_capacity);
2422  var_new_properties = new_properties;
2423 
2424  FillPropertyArrayWithUndefined(new_properties, var_length.value(),
2425  new_capacity);
2426 
2427  // |new_properties| is guaranteed to be in new space, so we can skip
2428  // the write barrier.
2429  CopyPropertyArrayValues(var_properties.value(), new_properties,
2430  var_length.value(), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER,
2431  DestroySource::kYes);
2432 
2433  TNode<Int32T> new_capacity_int32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(new_capacity);
2434  TNode<Int32T> new_length_and_hash_int32 =
2435  Word32Or(var_encoded_hash.value(), new_capacity_int32);
2436  StoreObjectField(new_properties, PropertyArray::kLengthAndHashOffset,
2437  SmiFromInt32(new_length_and_hash_int32));
2438  StoreObjectField(object, JSObject::kPropertiesOrHashOffset, new_properties);
2439  Comment("] Extend storage");
2440  Goto(&done);
2441  BIND(&done);
2442  return CAST(var_new_properties.value());
2443  }
2444 }
2445 
2446 void AccessorAssembler::EmitFastElementsBoundsCheck(
2447  TNode<JSObject> object, TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements,
2448  TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index, TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition,
2449  Label* miss) {
2450  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_length);
2451  Comment("Fast elements bounds check");
2452  Label if_array(this), length_loaded(this, &var_length);
2453  GotoIf(is_jsarray_condition, &if_array);
2454  {
2455  var_length = LoadAndUntagFixedArrayBaseLength(elements);
2456  Goto(&length_loaded);
2457  }
2458  BIND(&if_array);
2459  {
2460  var_length = PositiveSmiUntag(LoadFastJSArrayLength(CAST(object)));
2461  Goto(&length_loaded);
2462  }
2463  BIND(&length_loaded);
2464  GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThan(intptr_index, var_length.value()), miss);
2465 }
2466 
2467 void AccessorAssembler::EmitElementLoad(
2468  TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<Word32T> elements_kind,
2469  TNode<IntPtrT> intptr_index, TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition,
2470  Label* if_hole, Label* rebox_double, TVariable<Float64T>* var_double_value,
2471  Label* unimplemented_elements_kind, Label* out_of_bounds, Label* miss,
2472  ExitPoint* exit_point, LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
2473  Label if_rab_gsab_typed_array(this), if_typed_array(this), if_fast(this),
2474  if_fast_packed(this), if_fast_holey(this), if_fast_double(this),
2475  if_fast_holey_double(this), if_nonfast(this), if_dictionary(this);
2476  Branch(Int32GreaterThan(elements_kind,
2477  Int32Constant(LAST_ANY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS_KIND)),
2478  &if_nonfast, &if_fast);
2479 
2480  BIND(&if_fast);
2481  {
2482  TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadJSObjectElements(CAST(object));
2483  EmitFastElementsBoundsCheck(CAST(object), elements, intptr_index,
2484  is_jsarray_condition, out_of_bounds);
2485  int32_t kinds[] = {
2486  // Handled by if_fast_packed.
2487  PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS, PACKED_ELEMENTS, PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS,
2488  PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS, PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS, SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS,
2489  // Handled by if_fast_holey.
2490  HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS,
2491  HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS, HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS,
2492  // Handled by if_fast_double.
2493  PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS,
2494  // Handled by if_fast_holey_double.
2495  HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS};
2496  Label* labels[] = {// FAST_{SMI,}_ELEMENTS
2497  &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed,
2498  &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed, &if_fast_packed,
2499  // FAST_HOLEY_{SMI,}_ELEMENTS
2500  &if_fast_holey, &if_fast_holey, &if_fast_holey,
2501  &if_fast_holey, &if_fast_holey,
2502  // PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2503  &if_fast_double,
2504  // HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS
2505  &if_fast_holey_double};
2506  Switch(elements_kind, unimplemented_elements_kind, kinds, labels,
2507  arraysize(kinds));
2508 
2509  BIND(&if_fast_packed);
2510  {
2511  Comment("fast packed elements");
2512  exit_point->Return(
2513  access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas
2514  ? TrueConstant()
2515  : UnsafeLoadFixedArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index));
2516  }
2517 
2518  BIND(&if_fast_holey);
2519  {
2520  Comment("fast holey elements");
2521  TNode<Object> element =
2522  UnsafeLoadFixedArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index);
2523  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(element, TheHoleConstant()), if_hole);
2524  exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas ? TrueConstant()
2525  : element);
2526  }
2527 
2528  BIND(&if_fast_double);
2529  {
2530  Comment("packed double elements");
2531  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2532  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2533  } else {
2534  *var_double_value = LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(
2535  CAST(elements), intptr_index, nullptr, nullptr);
2536  Goto(rebox_double);
2537  }
2538  }
2539 
2540  BIND(&if_fast_holey_double);
2541  {
2542  Comment("holey double elements");
2543  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2544  LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(CAST(elements), intptr_index, nullptr,
2545  if_hole, MachineType::None());
2546  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2547  } else {
2548  *var_double_value = LoadFixedDoubleArrayElement(
2549  CAST(elements), intptr_index, if_hole, if_hole);
2550  Goto(rebox_double);
2551  }
2552  }
2553  }
2554 
2555  BIND(&if_nonfast);
2556  {
2557  Label uint8_elements(this), int8_elements(this), uint16_elements(this),
2558  int16_elements(this), uint32_elements(this), int32_elements(this),
2559  float32_elements(this), float64_elements(this), bigint64_elements(this),
2560  biguint64_elements(this), float16_elements(this);
2561  static_assert(LAST_ELEMENTS_KIND ==
2562  LAST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND);
2563  GotoIf(Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(
2564  elements_kind,
2565  Int32Constant(FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)),
2566  &if_rab_gsab_typed_array);
2567  GotoIf(Int32GreaterThanOrEqual(
2568  elements_kind,
2569  Int32Constant(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)),
2570  &if_typed_array);
2571  GotoIf(Word32Equal(elements_kind, Int32Constant(DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS)),
2572  &if_dictionary);
2573  Goto(unimplemented_elements_kind);
2574 
2575  BIND(&if_dictionary);
2576  {
2577  Comment("dictionary elements");
2578  if (Is64()) {
2579  GotoIf(UintPtrLessThan(IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex),
2580  intptr_index),
2581  out_of_bounds);
2582  } else {
2583  GotoIf(IntPtrLessThan(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(0)), out_of_bounds);
2584  }
2585 
2586  TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadJSObjectElements(CAST(object));
2587  TNode<Object> value = BasicLoadNumberDictionaryElement(
2588  CAST(elements), intptr_index, miss, if_hole);
2589  exit_point->Return(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas ? TrueConstant()
2590  : value);
2591  }
2592  {
2593  TVARIABLE(RawPtrT, data_ptr);
2594  BIND(&if_rab_gsab_typed_array);
2595  {
2596  Comment("rab gsab typed elements");
2597  Label variable_length(this), normal(this), length_check_ok(this);
2598 
2599  TNode<JSTypedArray> array = CAST(object);
2600  TNode<JSArrayBuffer> buffer = LoadJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(array);
2601 
2602  // Bounds check (incl. detachedness check).
2603  TNode<UintPtrT> length =
2604  LoadVariableLengthJSTypedArrayLength(array, buffer, miss);
2605  Branch(UintPtrLessThan(intptr_index, length), &length_check_ok,
2606  out_of_bounds);
2607  BIND(&length_check_ok);
2608  {
2609  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2610  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2611  } else {
2612  data_ptr = LoadJSTypedArrayDataPtr(array);
2613  Label* elements_kind_labels[] = {
2614  &uint8_elements, &uint8_elements, &int8_elements,
2615  &uint16_elements, &int16_elements, &uint32_elements,
2616  &int32_elements, &float32_elements, &float64_elements,
2617  &bigint64_elements, &biguint64_elements, &float16_elements,
2618  };
2619  int32_t elements_kinds[] = {
2620  RAB_GSAB_UINT8_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS,
2621  RAB_GSAB_INT8_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_UINT16_ELEMENTS,
2622  RAB_GSAB_INT16_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_UINT32_ELEMENTS,
2623  RAB_GSAB_INT32_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT32_ELEMENTS,
2624  RAB_GSAB_FLOAT64_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_BIGINT64_ELEMENTS,
2625  RAB_GSAB_BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, RAB_GSAB_FLOAT16_ELEMENTS};
2626  const size_t kTypedElementsKindCount =
2627  LAST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND -
2628  FIRST_RAB_GSAB_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1;
2629  DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kinds));
2630  DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kind_labels));
2631  Switch(elements_kind, miss, elements_kinds, elements_kind_labels,
2632  kTypedElementsKindCount);
2633  }
2634  }
2635  }
2636  BIND(&if_typed_array);
2637  {
2638  Comment("typed elements");
2639  // Check if buffer has been detached.
2640  TNode<JSArrayBuffer> buffer = LoadJSArrayBufferViewBuffer(CAST(object));
2641  GotoIf(IsDetachedBuffer(buffer), miss);
2642 
2643  // Bounds check.
2644  TNode<UintPtrT> length = LoadJSTypedArrayLength(CAST(object));
2645  GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThan(intptr_index, length), out_of_bounds);
2646  if (access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2647  exit_point->Return(TrueConstant());
2648  } else {
2649  data_ptr = LoadJSTypedArrayDataPtr(CAST(object));
2650 
2651  Label* elements_kind_labels[] = {
2652  &uint8_elements, &uint8_elements, &int8_elements,
2653  &uint16_elements, &int16_elements, &uint32_elements,
2654  &int32_elements, &float32_elements, &float64_elements,
2655  &bigint64_elements, &biguint64_elements, &float16_elements};
2656  int32_t elements_kinds[] = {
2657  UINT8_ELEMENTS, UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS, INT8_ELEMENTS,
2658  UINT16_ELEMENTS, INT16_ELEMENTS, UINT32_ELEMENTS,
2659  INT32_ELEMENTS, FLOAT32_ELEMENTS, FLOAT64_ELEMENTS,
2660  BIGINT64_ELEMENTS, BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS, FLOAT16_ELEMENTS};
2661  const size_t kTypedElementsKindCount =
2662  LAST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND -
2663  FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND + 1;
2664  DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kinds));
2665  DCHECK_EQ(kTypedElementsKindCount, arraysize(elements_kind_labels));
2666  Switch(elements_kind, miss, elements_kinds, elements_kind_labels,
2667  kTypedElementsKindCount);
2668  }
2669  }
2670  if (access_mode != LoadAccessMode::kHas) {
2671  BIND(&uint8_elements);
2672  {
2673  Comment("UINT8_ELEMENTS"); // Handles UINT8_CLAMPED_ELEMENTS too.
2674  TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Uint8T>(data_ptr.value(), intptr_index);
2675  exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2676  }
2677  BIND(&int8_elements);
2678  {
2679  Comment("INT8_ELEMENTS");
2680  TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Int8T>(data_ptr.value(), intptr_index);
2681  exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2682  }
2683  BIND(&uint16_elements);
2684  {
2685  Comment("UINT16_ELEMENTS");
2686  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(1));
2687  TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Uint16T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2688  exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2689  }
2690  BIND(&int16_elements);
2691  {
2692  Comment("INT16_ELEMENTS");
2693  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(1));
2694  TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Int16T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2695  exit_point->Return(SmiFromInt32(element));
2696  }
2697  BIND(&uint32_elements);
2698  {
2699  Comment("UINT32_ELEMENTS");
2700  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(2));
2701  TNode<Uint32T> element = Load<Uint32T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2702  exit_point->Return(ChangeUint32ToTagged(element));
2703  }
2704  BIND(&int32_elements);
2705  {
2706  Comment("INT32_ELEMENTS");
2707  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(2));
2708  TNode<Int32T> element = Load<Int32T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2709  exit_point->Return(ChangeInt32ToTagged(element));
2710  }
2711  BIND(&float16_elements);
2712  {
2713  Comment("FLOAT16_ELEMENTS");
2714  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(1));
2715  TNode<Float16RawBitsT> raw_element =
2716  Load<Float16RawBitsT>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2717  *var_double_value = ChangeFloat16ToFloat64(raw_element);
2718  Goto(rebox_double);
2719  }
2720  BIND(&float32_elements);
2721  {
2722  Comment("FLOAT32_ELEMENTS");
2723  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(2));
2724  TNode<Float32T> element = Load<Float32T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2725  *var_double_value = ChangeFloat32ToFloat64(element);
2726  Goto(rebox_double);
2727  }
2728  BIND(&float64_elements);
2729  {
2730  Comment("FLOAT64_ELEMENTS");
2731  TNode<IntPtrT> index = WordShl(intptr_index, IntPtrConstant(3));
2732  TNode<Float64T> element = Load<Float64T>(data_ptr.value(), index);
2733  *var_double_value = element;
2734  Goto(rebox_double);
2735  }
2736  BIND(&bigint64_elements);
2737  {
2738  Comment("BIGINT64_ELEMENTS");
2739  exit_point->Return(LoadFixedTypedArrayElementAsTagged(
2740  data_ptr.value(), Unsigned(intptr_index), BIGINT64_ELEMENTS));
2741  }
2742  BIND(&biguint64_elements);
2743  {
2744  Comment("BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS");
2745  exit_point->Return(LoadFixedTypedArrayElementAsTagged(
2746  data_ptr.value(), Unsigned(intptr_index), BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS));
2747  }
2748  }
2749  }
2750  }
2751 }
2752 
2753 void AccessorAssembler::InvalidateValidityCellIfPrototype(
2754  TNode<Map> map, std::optional<TNode<Uint32T>> maybe_bitfield3) {
2755  Label is_prototype(this), cont(this);
2756  TNode<Uint32T> bitfield3;
2757  if (maybe_bitfield3) {
2758  bitfield3 = maybe_bitfield3.value();
2759  } else {
2760  bitfield3 = LoadMapBitField3(map);
2761  }
2762 
2763  Branch(IsSetWord32(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::IsPrototypeMapBit::kMask),
2764  &is_prototype, &cont);
2765 
2766  BIND(&is_prototype);
2767  {
2768  TNode<Object> maybe_prototype_info =
2769  LoadObjectField(map, Map::kTransitionsOrPrototypeInfoOffset);
2770  // If there's no prototype info then there's nothing to invalidate.
2771  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_prototype_info), &cont);
2772 
2773  TNode<ExternalReference> function = ExternalConstant(
2774  ExternalReference::invalidate_prototype_chains_function());
2775  CallCFunction(function, MachineType::AnyTagged(),
2776  std::make_pair(MachineType::AnyTagged(), map));
2777  Goto(&cont);
2778  }
2779  BIND(&cont);
2780 }
2781 
2782 void AccessorAssembler::GenericElementLoad(
2783  TNode<JSAnyNotSmi> lookup_start_object, TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
2784  TNode<Int32T> lookup_start_object_instance_type, TNode<IntPtrT> index,
2785  Label* slow) {
2786  Comment("integer index");
2787 
2788  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
2789 
2790  Label if_custom(this), if_element_hole(this), if_oob(this);
2791  Label return_undefined(this);
2792  // Receivers requiring non-standard element accesses (interceptors, access
2793  // checks, strings and string wrappers, proxies) are handled in the runtime.
2794  GotoIf(
2795  IsCustomElementsReceiverInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type),
2796  &if_custom);
2797  TNode<Int32T> elements_kind = LoadMapElementsKind(lookup_start_object_map);
2798  TNode<BoolT> is_jsarray_condition =
2799  IsJSArrayInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type);
2800  TVARIABLE(Float64T, var_double_value);
2801  Label rebox_double(this, &var_double_value);
2802 
2803  // Unimplemented elements kinds fall back to a runtime call.
2804  Label* unimplemented_elements_kind = slow;
2805  EmitElementLoad(lookup_start_object, elements_kind, index,
2806  is_jsarray_condition, &if_element_hole, &rebox_double,
2807  &var_double_value, unimplemented_elements_kind, &if_oob, slow,
2808  &direct_exit);
2809 
2810  BIND(&rebox_double);
2811  Return(AllocateHeapNumberWithValue(var_double_value.value()));
2812 
2813  BIND(&if_oob);
2814  {
2815  Comment("out of bounds");
2816  // On TypedArrays, all OOB loads (positive and negative) return undefined
2817  // without ever checking the prototype chain.
2818  GotoIf(IsJSTypedArrayInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type),
2819  &return_undefined);
2820  // Positive OOB indices within elements index range are effectively the same
2821  // as hole loads. Larger keys and negative keys are named loads.
2822  if (Is64()) {
2823  Branch(UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(index,
2824  IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex)),
2825  &if_element_hole, slow);
2826  } else {
2827  Branch(IntPtrLessThan(index, IntPtrConstant(0)), slow, &if_element_hole);
2828  }
2829  }
2830 
2831  BIND(&if_element_hole);
2832  {
2833  Comment("found the hole");
2834  BranchIfPrototypesHaveNoElements(lookup_start_object_map, &return_undefined,
2835  slow);
2836  }
2837 
2838  BIND(&if_custom);
2839  {
2840  Comment("check if string");
2841  GotoIfNot(IsStringInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type), slow);
2842  Comment("load string character");
2843  TNode<IntPtrT> length = LoadStringLengthAsWord(CAST(lookup_start_object));
2844  GotoIfNot(UintPtrLessThan(index, length), slow);
2845  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kStringCharAt, NoContextConstant(),
2846  lookup_start_object, index);
2847  }
2848 
2849  BIND(&return_undefined);
2850  Return(UndefinedConstant());
2851 }
2852 
2853 void AccessorAssembler::GenericPropertyLoad(
2854  TNode<JSAnyNotSmi> lookup_start_object, TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
2855  TNode<Int32T> lookup_start_object_instance_type, const LoadICParameters* p,
2856  Label* slow, UseStubCache use_stub_cache) {
2857  DCHECK_EQ(lookup_start_object, p->lookup_start_object());
2858  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
2859 
2860  Comment("key is unique name");
2861  Label if_found_on_lookup_start_object(this), if_property_dictionary(this),
2862  lookup_prototype_chain(this), special_receiver(this);
2863  TVARIABLE(Uint32T, var_details);
2864  TVARIABLE(Object, var_value);
2865 
2866  TNode<Name> name = CAST(p->name());
2867 
2868  // Receivers requiring non-standard accesses (interceptors, access
2869  // checks, strings and string wrappers) are handled in the runtime.
2870  GotoIf(IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(lookup_start_object_instance_type),
2871  &special_receiver);
2872 
2873  // Check if the lookup_start_object has fast or slow properties.
2874  TNode<Uint32T> bitfield3 = LoadMapBitField3(lookup_start_object_map);
2875  GotoIf(IsSetWord32<Map::Bits3::IsDictionaryMapBit>(bitfield3),
2876  &if_property_dictionary);
2877 
2878  {
2879  // Try looking up the property on the lookup_start_object; if unsuccessful,
2880  // look for a handler in the stub cache.
2881  TNode<DescriptorArray> descriptors =
2882  LoadMapDescriptors(lookup_start_object_map);
2883 
2884  Label if_descriptor_found(this), try_stub_cache(this);
2885  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
2886  Label* notfound = use_stub_cache == kUseStubCache ? &try_stub_cache
2887  : &lookup_prototype_chain;
2888  DescriptorLookup(name, descriptors, bitfield3, &if_descriptor_found,
2889  &var_name_index, notfound);
2890 
2891  BIND(&if_descriptor_found);
2892  {
2893  LoadPropertyFromFastObject(lookup_start_object, lookup_start_object_map,
2894  descriptors, var_name_index.value(),
2895  &var_details, &var_value);
2896  Goto(&if_found_on_lookup_start_object);
2897  }
2898 
2899  if (use_stub_cache == kUseStubCache) {
2900  DCHECK_EQ(lookup_start_object, p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
2901  Label stub_cache(this);
2902  BIND(&try_stub_cache);
2903  // When there is no feedback vector don't use stub cache.
2904  GotoIfNot(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &stub_cache);
2905  // Fall back to the slow path for private symbols.
2906  Branch(IsPrivateSymbol(name), slow, &lookup_prototype_chain);
2907 
2908  BIND(&stub_cache);
2909  Comment("stub cache probe for fast property load");
2910  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
2911  Label found_handler(this, &var_handler), stub_cache_miss(this);
2912  TryProbeStubCache(isolate()->load_stub_cache(), lookup_start_object,
2913  lookup_start_object_map, name, &found_handler,
2914  &var_handler, &stub_cache_miss);
2915  BIND(&found_handler);
2916  {
2917  LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
2918  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &stub_cache_miss,
2919  &direct_exit);
2920  }
2921 
2922  BIND(&stub_cache_miss);
2923  {
2924  // TODO(jkummerow): Check if the property exists on the prototype
2925  // chain. If it doesn't, then there's no point in missing.
2926  Comment("KeyedLoadGeneric_miss");
2927  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kKeyedLoadIC_Miss, p->context(),
2928  p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(), name, p->slot(),
2929  p->vector());
2930  }
2931  }
2932  }
2933 
2934  BIND(&if_property_dictionary);
2935  {
2936  Comment("dictionary property load");
2937  // We checked for LAST_CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_RECEIVER before, which rules out
2938  // seeing global objects here (which would need special handling).
2939 
2940  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_name_index);
2941  Label dictionary_found(this, &var_name_index);
2942  TNode<PropertyDictionary> properties =
2943  CAST(LoadSlowProperties(CAST(lookup_start_object)));
2944  NameDictionaryLookup<PropertyDictionary>(properties, name,
2945  &dictionary_found, &var_name_index,
2946  &lookup_prototype_chain);
2947  BIND(&dictionary_found);
2948  {
2949  LoadPropertyFromDictionary<PropertyDictionary>(
2950  properties, var_name_index.value(), &var_details, &var_value);
2951  Goto(&if_found_on_lookup_start_object);
2952  }
2953  }
2954 
2955  BIND(&if_found_on_lookup_start_object);
2956  {
2957  TNode<Object> value = CallGetterIfAccessor(
2958  var_value.value(), CAST(lookup_start_object), var_details.value(),
2959  p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), slow);
2960  Return(value);
2961  }
2962 
2963  BIND(&lookup_prototype_chain);
2964  {
2965  TVARIABLE(Map, var_holder_map);
2966  TVARIABLE(Int32T, var_holder_instance_type);
2967  Label return_undefined(this), is_private_symbol(this);
2968  Label loop(this, {&var_holder_map, &var_holder_instance_type});
2969 
2970  var_holder_map = lookup_start_object_map;
2971  var_holder_instance_type = lookup_start_object_instance_type;
2972  GotoIf(IsPrivateSymbol(name), &is_private_symbol);
2973 
2974  Goto(&loop);
2975  BIND(&loop);
2976  {
2977  // Bailout if it can be an integer indexed exotic case.
2978  GotoIf(InstanceTypeEqual(var_holder_instance_type.value(),
2979  JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE),
2980  slow);
2981  TNode<HeapObject> proto = LoadMapPrototype(var_holder_map.value());
2982  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(proto, NullConstant()), &return_undefined);
2983  TNode<Map> proto_map = LoadMap(proto);
2984  TNode<Uint16T> proto_instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(proto_map);
2985  var_holder_map = proto_map;
2986  var_holder_instance_type = proto_instance_type;
2987  Label next_proto(this), return_value(this, &var_value), goto_slow(this);
2988  TryGetOwnProperty(p->context(), p->receiver(), CAST(proto), proto_map,
2989  proto_instance_type, name, &return_value, &var_value,
2990  &next_proto, &goto_slow);
2991 
2992  // This trampoline and the next are required to appease Turbofan's
2993  // variable merging.
2994  BIND(&next_proto);
2995  Goto(&loop);
2996 
2997  BIND(&goto_slow);
2998  Goto(slow);
2999 
3000  BIND(&return_value);
3001  Return(var_value.value());
3002  }
3003 
3004  BIND(&is_private_symbol);
3005  {
3006  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsPrivateSymbol(name));
3007 
3008  // For private names that don't exist on the receiver, we bail
3009  // to the runtime to throw. For private symbols, we just return
3010  // undefined.
3011  Branch(IsPrivateName(CAST(name)), slow, &return_undefined);
3012  }
3013 
3014  BIND(&return_undefined);
3015  Return(UndefinedConstant());
3016  }
3017 
3018  BIND(&special_receiver);
3019  {
3020  // TODO(ishell): Consider supporting WasmObjects.
3021  // TODO(jkummerow): Consider supporting JSModuleNamespace.
3022  GotoIfNot(
3023  InstanceTypeEqual(lookup_start_object_instance_type, JS_PROXY_TYPE),
3024  slow);
3025 
3026  // Private field/symbol lookup is not supported.
3027  GotoIf(IsPrivateSymbol(name), slow);
3028 
3029  direct_exit.ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kProxyGetProperty, p->context(),
3030  lookup_start_object, name, p->receiver(),
3031  SmiConstant(OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined));
3032  }
3033 }
3034 
3035 //////////////////// Stub cache access helpers.
3036 
3037 enum AccessorAssembler::StubCacheTable : int {
3038  kPrimary = static_cast<int>(StubCache::kPrimary),
3039  kSecondary = static_cast<int>(StubCache::kSecondary)
3040 };
3041 
3042 TNode<IntPtrT> AccessorAssembler::StubCachePrimaryOffset(TNode<Name> name,
3043  TNode<Map> map) {
3044  // Compute the hash of the name (use entire hash field).
3045  TNode<Uint32T> raw_hash_field = LoadNameRawHash(name);
3046  CSA_DCHECK(this,
3047  Word32Equal(Word32And(raw_hash_field,
3048  Int32Constant(Name::kHashNotComputedMask)),
3049  Int32Constant(0)));
3050 
3051  // Using only the low bits in 64-bit mode is unlikely to increase the
3052  // risk of collision even if the heap is spread over an area larger than
3053  // 4Gb (and not at all if it isn't).
3054  TNode<IntPtrT> map_word = BitcastTaggedToWord(map);
3055 
3056  TNode<Int32T> map32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(
3057  WordXor(map_word, WordShr(map_word, StubCache::kPrimaryTableBits))));
3058  // Base the offset on a simple combination of name and map.
3059  TNode<Word32T> hash = Int32Add(raw_hash_field, map32);
3060  uint32_t mask = (StubCache::kPrimaryTableSize - 1)
3061  << StubCache::kCacheIndexShift;
3062  TNode<UintPtrT> result =
3063  ChangeUint32ToWord(Word32And(hash, Int32Constant(mask)));
3064  return Signed(result);
3065 }
3066 
3067 TNode<IntPtrT> AccessorAssembler::StubCacheSecondaryOffset(TNode<Name> name,
3068  TNode<Map> map) {
3069  // See v8::internal::StubCache::SecondaryOffset().
3070 
3071  // Use the seed from the primary cache in the secondary cache.
3072  TNode<Int32T> name32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWord(name));
3073  TNode<Int32T> map32 = TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWord(map));
3074  // Base the offset on a simple combination of name and map.
3075  TNode<Word32T> hash_a = Int32Add(map32, name32);
3076  TNode<Word32T> hash_b = Word32Shr(hash_a, StubCache::kSecondaryTableBits);
3077  TNode<Word32T> hash = Int32Add(hash_a, hash_b);
3078  int32_t mask = (StubCache::kSecondaryTableSize - 1)
3079  << StubCache::kCacheIndexShift;
3080  TNode<UintPtrT> result =
3081  ChangeUint32ToWord(Word32And(hash, Int32Constant(mask)));
3082  return Signed(result);
3083 }
3084 
3085 void AccessorAssembler::TryProbeStubCacheTable(
3086  StubCache* stub_cache, StubCacheTable table_id, TNode<IntPtrT> entry_offset,
3087  TNode<Object> name, TNode<Map> map, Label* if_handler,
3088  TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler, Label* if_miss) {
3089  StubCache::Table table = static_cast<StubCache::Table>(table_id);
3090  // The {table_offset} holds the entry offset times four (due to masking
3091  // and shifting optimizations).
3092  const int kMultiplier =
3093  sizeof(StubCache::Entry) >> StubCache::kCacheIndexShift;
3094  entry_offset = IntPtrMul(entry_offset, IntPtrConstant(kMultiplier));
3095 
3096  TNode<ExternalReference> key_base = ExternalConstant(
3097  ExternalReference::Create(stub_cache->key_reference(table)));
3098 
3099  // Check that the key in the entry matches the name.
3100  DCHECK_EQ(0, offsetof(StubCache::Entry, key));
3101  TNode<HeapObject> cached_key =
3102  CAST(Load(MachineType::TaggedPointer(), key_base, entry_offset));
3103  GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(name, cached_key), if_miss);
3104 
3105  // Check that the map in the entry matches.
3106  TNode<Object> cached_map = Load<Object>(
3107  key_base,
3108  IntPtrAdd(entry_offset, IntPtrConstant(offsetof(StubCache::Entry, map))));
3109  GotoIf(TaggedNotEqual(map, cached_map), if_miss);
3110 
3111  TNode<MaybeObject> handler = ReinterpretCast<MaybeObject>(
3112  Load(MachineType::AnyTagged(), key_base,
3113  IntPtrAdd(entry_offset,
3114  IntPtrConstant(offsetof(StubCache::Entry, value)))));
3115 
3116  // We found the handler.
3117  *var_handler = handler;
3118  Goto(if_handler);
3119 }
3120 
3121 void AccessorAssembler::TryProbeStubCache(StubCache* stub_cache,
3122  TNode<JSAny> lookup_start_object,
3123  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
3124  TNode<Name> name, Label* if_handler,
3125  TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler,
3126  Label* if_miss) {
3127  Label try_secondary(this), miss(this);
3128 
3129  Counters* counters = isolate()->counters();
3130  IncrementCounter(counters->megamorphic_stub_cache_probes(), 1);
3131 
3132  // Probe the primary table.
3133  TNode<IntPtrT> primary_offset =
3134  StubCachePrimaryOffset(name, lookup_start_object_map);
3135  TryProbeStubCacheTable(stub_cache, kPrimary, primary_offset, name,
3136  lookup_start_object_map, if_handler, var_handler,
3137  &try_secondary);
3138 
3139  BIND(&try_secondary);
3140  {
3141  // Probe the secondary table.
3142  TNode<IntPtrT> secondary_offset =
3143  StubCacheSecondaryOffset(name, lookup_start_object_map);
3144  TryProbeStubCacheTable(stub_cache, kSecondary, secondary_offset, name,
3145  lookup_start_object_map, if_handler, var_handler,
3146  &miss);
3147  }
3148 
3149  BIND(&miss);
3150  {
3151  IncrementCounter(counters->megamorphic_stub_cache_misses(), 1);
3152  Goto(if_miss);
3153  }
3154 }
3155 
3156 //////////////////// Entry points into private implementation (one per stub).
3157 
3158 void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC_BytecodeHandler(const LazyLoadICParameters* p,
3159  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
3160  // Must be kept in sync with LoadIC.
3161 
3162  // This function is hand-tuned to omit frame construction for common cases,
3163  // e.g.: monomorphic field and constant loads through smi handlers.
3164  // Polymorphic ICs with a hit in the first two entries also omit frames.
3165  // TODO(jgruber): Frame omission is fragile and can be affected by minor
3166  // changes in control flow and logic. We currently have no way of ensuring
3167  // that no frame is constructed, so it's easy to break this optimization by
3168  // accident.
3169  Label stub_call(this, Label::kDeferred), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3170  no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3171 
3172  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3173 
3174  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3175  LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
3176 
3177  // Inlined fast path.
3178  {
3179  Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_fast");
3180 
3181  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3182  Label try_polymorphic(this), if_handler(this, &var_handler);
3183 
3184  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3185  MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3186  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3187  p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3188  &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3189 
3190  BIND(&if_handler);
3191  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss, exit_point);
3192 
3193  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3194  {
3195  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback =
3196  GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3197  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &stub_call);
3198  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3199  &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3200  }
3201  }
3202 
3203  BIND(&stub_call);
3204  {
3205  Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_noninlined");
3206 
3207  // Call into the stub that implements the non-inlined parts of LoadIC.
3208  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_Noninlined, p->context(),
3209  p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(),
3210  p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3211  }
3212 
3213  BIND(&no_feedback);
3214  {
3215  Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_nofeedback");
3216  // Call into the stub that implements the non-inlined parts of LoadIC.
3217  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_NoFeedback, p->context(),
3218  p->receiver(), p->name(),
3219  SmiConstant(FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadProperty));
3220  }
3221 
3222  BIND(&miss);
3223  {
3224  Comment("LoadIC_BytecodeHandler_miss");
3225 
3226  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, p->context(),
3227  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->slot(),
3228  p->vector());
3229  }
3230 }
3231 
3232 void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3233  // Must be kept in sync with LoadIC_BytecodeHandler.
3234 
3235  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3236 
3237  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3238  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), non_inlined(this, Label::kDeferred),
3239  try_polymorphic(this), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3240  no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3241 
3242  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3243  LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
3244 
3245  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3246 
3247  // Check monomorphic case.
3248  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3249  MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3250  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3251  p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3252  &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3253  BIND(&if_handler);
3254  {
3255  LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3256  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
3257  }
3258 
3259  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3260  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3261  {
3262  // Check polymorphic case.
3263  Comment("LoadIC_try_polymorphic");
3264  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &non_inlined);
3265  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3266  &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3267  }
3268 
3269  BIND(&non_inlined);
3270  {
3271  LoadIC_Noninlined(p, lookup_start_object_map, strong_feedback, &var_handler,
3272  &if_handler, &miss, &direct_exit);
3273  }
3274 
3275  BIND(&no_feedback);
3276  {
3277  Comment("LoadIC_nofeedback");
3278  // Call into the stub that implements the non-inlined parts of LoadIC.
3279  direct_exit.ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_NoFeedback, p->context(),
3280  p->receiver(), p->name(),
3281  SmiConstant(FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadProperty));
3282  }
3283 
3284  BIND(&miss);
3285  direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, p->context(),
3286  p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(),
3287  p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3288 }
3289 
3290 void AccessorAssembler::LoadSuperIC(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3291  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3292 
3293  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3294  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), no_feedback(this),
3295  non_inlined(this, Label::kDeferred), try_polymorphic(this),
3296  miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3297 
3298  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3299 
3300  // The lookup start object cannot be a SMI, since it's the home object's
3301  // prototype, and it's not possible to set SMIs as prototypes.
3302  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(p->lookup_start_object()));
3303  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3304 
3305  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3306  MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3307  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3308  p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3309  &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3310 
3311  BIND(&if_handler);
3312  {
3313  LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3314  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
3315  }
3316 
3317  BIND(&no_feedback);
3318  { LoadSuperIC_NoFeedback(p); }
3319 
3320  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3321  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3322  {
3323  Comment("LoadSuperIC_try_polymorphic");
3324  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &non_inlined);
3325  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3326  &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3327  }
3328 
3329  BIND(&non_inlined);
3330  {
3331  // LoadIC_Noninlined can be used here, since it handles the
3332  // lookup_start_object != receiver case gracefully.
3333  LoadIC_Noninlined(p, lookup_start_object_map, strong_feedback, &var_handler,
3334  &if_handler, &miss, &direct_exit);
3335  }
3336 
3337  BIND(&miss);
3338  direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadWithReceiverIC_Miss, p->context(),
3339  p->receiver(), p->lookup_start_object(),
3340  p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3341 }
3342 
3343 void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC_Noninlined(const LoadICParameters* p,
3344  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map,
3345  TNode<HeapObject> feedback,
3346  TVariable<MaybeObject>* var_handler,
3347  Label* if_handler, Label* miss,
3348  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
3349  // Not monomorphic -- this cases is handled in the bytecode handler.
3350  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedNotEqual(lookup_start_object_map, feedback));
3351  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32BinaryNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(feedback))));
3352  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, var_handler->rep());
3353 
3354  {
3355  Label try_megamorphic(this), try_megadom(this);
3356  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
3357  &try_megamorphic);
3358  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(feedback, MegaDOMSymbolConstant()), &try_megadom);
3359  Goto(miss);
3360 
3361  BIND(&try_megamorphic);
3362  {
3363  TryProbeStubCache(isolate()->load_stub_cache(), p->lookup_start_object(),
3364  lookup_start_object_map, CAST(p->name()), if_handler,
3365  var_handler, miss);
3366  }
3367 
3368  BIND(&try_megadom);
3369  {
3370  TryMegaDOMCase(p->lookup_start_object(), lookup_start_object_map,
3371  var_handler, p->vector(), p->slot(), miss, exit_point);
3372  }
3373  }
3374 }
3375 
3376 void AccessorAssembler::LoadIC_NoFeedback(const LoadICParameters* p,
3377  TNode<Smi> ic_kind) {
3378  Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3379  TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object();
3380  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(lookup_start_object), &miss);
3381  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3382  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3383 
3384  TNode<Uint16T> instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map);
3385 
3386  {
3387  // Special case for Function.prototype load, because it's very common
3388  // for ICs that are only executed once (MyFunc.prototype.foo = ...).
3389  Label not_function_prototype(this, Label::kDeferred);
3390  GotoIfNot(IsJSFunctionInstanceType(instance_type), &not_function_prototype);
3391  GotoIfNot(IsPrototypeString(p->name()), &not_function_prototype);
3392 
3393  GotoIfPrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(CAST(lookup_start_object),
3394  lookup_start_object_map,
3395  &not_function_prototype);
3396  Return(LoadJSFunctionPrototype(CAST(lookup_start_object), &miss));
3397  BIND(&not_function_prototype);
3398  }
3399 
3400  GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3401  instance_type, p, &miss, kDontUseStubCache);
3402 
3403  BIND(&miss);
3404  {
3405  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadNoFeedbackIC_Miss, p->context(),
3406  p->receiver(), p->name(), ic_kind);
3407  }
3408 }
3409 
3410 void AccessorAssembler::LoadSuperIC_NoFeedback(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3411  Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3412  TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->lookup_start_object();
3413 
3414  // The lookup start object cannot be a SMI, since it's the home object's
3415  // prototype, and it's not possible to set SMIs as prototypes.
3416  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3417  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3418 
3419  TNode<Uint16T> instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map);
3420 
3421  GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3422  instance_type, p, &miss, kDontUseStubCache);
3423 
3424  BIND(&miss);
3425  {
3426  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadWithReceiverNoFeedbackIC_Miss, p->context(),
3427  p->receiver(), p->lookup_start_object(), p->name());
3428  }
3429 }

3431 void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC(TNode<HeapObject> maybe_feedback_vector,
3432  const LazyNode<TaggedIndex>& lazy_slot,
3433  const LazyNode<Context>& lazy_context,
3434  const LazyNode<Name>& lazy_name,
3435  TypeofMode typeof_mode,
3436  ExitPoint* exit_point) {
3437  Label try_handler(this, Label::kDeferred), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3438  no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3439 
3440  GotoIf(IsUndefined(maybe_feedback_vector), &no_feedback);
3441  {
3442  TNode<TaggedIndex> slot = lazy_slot();
3443 
3444  {
3445  TNode<FeedbackVector> vector = CAST(maybe_feedback_vector);
3446  LoadGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase(vector, slot, lazy_context, exit_point,
3447  &try_handler, &miss);
3448 
3449  BIND(&try_handler);
3450  LoadGlobalIC_TryHandlerCase(vector, slot, lazy_context, lazy_name,
3451  typeof_mode, exit_point, &miss);
3452  }
3453 
3454  BIND(&miss);
3455  {
3456  Comment("LoadGlobalIC_MissCase");
3457  TNode<Context> context = lazy_context();
3458  TNode<Name> name = lazy_name();
3459  exit_point->ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadGlobalIC_Miss, context, name,
3460  slot, maybe_feedback_vector,
3461  SmiConstant(typeof_mode));
3462  }
3463  }
3464 
3465  BIND(&no_feedback);
3466  {
3467  int ic_kind =
3468  static_cast<int>((typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kInside)
3469  ? FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalInsideTypeof
3470  : FeedbackSlotKind::kLoadGlobalNotInsideTypeof);
3471  exit_point->ReturnCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadGlobalIC_NoFeedback,
3472  lazy_context(), lazy_name(),
3473  SmiConstant(ic_kind));
3474  }
3475 }
3476 
3477 void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase(
3478  TNode<FeedbackVector> vector, TNode<TaggedIndex> slot,
3479  const LazyNode<Context>& lazy_context, ExitPoint* exit_point,
3480  Label* try_handler, Label* miss) {
3481  Comment("LoadGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase");
3482 
3483  Label if_lexical_var(this), if_property_cell(this);
3484  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_weak_ref = LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot);
3485  Branch(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_weak_ref), &if_lexical_var, &if_property_cell);
3486 
3487  BIND(&if_property_cell);
3488  {
3489  // This branch also handles the "handler mode": the weak reference is
3490  // cleared, the feedback extra is the handler. In that case we jump to
3491  // try_handler. (See FeedbackNexus::ConfigureHandlerMode.)
3492  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_weak_ref));
3493  TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell =
3494  CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_weak_ref, try_handler));
3495  TNode<Object> value =
3496  LoadObjectField(property_cell, PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
3497  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(value, PropertyCellHoleConstant()), miss);
3498  exit_point->Return(value);
3499  }
3500 
3501  BIND(&if_lexical_var);
3502  {
3503  // This branch handles the "lexical variable mode": the feedback is a SMI
3504  // encoding the variable location. (See
3505  // FeedbackNexus::ConfigureLexicalVarMode.)
3506  Comment("Load lexical variable");
3507  TNode<IntPtrT> lexical_handler = SmiUntag(CAST(maybe_weak_ref));
3508  TNode<IntPtrT> context_index =
3509  Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::ContextIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3510  TNode<IntPtrT> slot_index =
3511  Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::SlotIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3512  TNode<Context> context = lazy_context();
3513  TNode<Context> script_context = LoadScriptContext(context, context_index);
3514  TNode<Object> result = LoadContextElement(script_context, slot_index);
3515  exit_point->Return(result);
3516  }
3517 }
3518 
3519 void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC_TryHandlerCase(
3520  TNode<FeedbackVector> vector, TNode<TaggedIndex> slot,
3521  const LazyNode<Context>& lazy_context, const LazyNode<Name>& lazy_name,
3522  TypeofMode typeof_mode, ExitPoint* exit_point, Label* miss) {
3523  Comment("LoadGlobalIC_TryHandlerCase");
3524 
3525  Label call_handler(this), non_smi(this);
3526 
3527  TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
3528  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot, kTaggedSize);
3529  TNode<Object> handler = CAST(feedback_element);
3530  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(handler, UninitializedSymbolConstant()), miss);
3531 
3532  OnNonExistent on_nonexistent = typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kNotInside
3533  ? OnNonExistent::kThrowReferenceError
3534  : OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined;
3535 
3536  TNode<Context> context = lazy_context();
3537  TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
3538  TNode<JSGlobalProxy> receiver = CAST(
3539  LoadContextElementNoCell(native_context, Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX));
3540  TNode<JSAny> global =
3541  CAST(LoadContextElementNoCell(native_context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
3542 
3543  LazyLoadICParameters p([=] { return context; }, receiver, lazy_name,
3544  [=] { return slot; }, vector, global);
3545 
3546  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&p, handler, miss, exit_point, ICMode::kGlobalIC,
3547  on_nonexistent);
3548 }
3549 
3550 void AccessorAssembler::ScriptContextTableLookup(
3551  TNode<Name> name, TNode<NativeContext> native_context, Label* found_hole,
3552  Label* not_found) {
3553  TNode<ScriptContextTable> script_context_table =
3554  CAST(LoadContextElementNoCell(native_context,
3555  Context::SCRIPT_CONTEXT_TABLE_INDEX));
3556  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, context_index, IntPtrConstant(-1));
3557  Label loop(this, &context_index);
3558  TNode<IntPtrT> num_script_contexts = PositiveSmiUntag(CAST(LoadObjectField(
3559  script_context_table, offsetof(ScriptContextTable, length_))));
3560  Goto(&loop);
3561 
3562  BIND(&loop);
3563  {
3564  context_index = IntPtrAdd(context_index.value(), IntPtrConstant(1));
3565  GotoIf(IntPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(context_index.value(), num_script_contexts),
3566  not_found);
3567 
3568  TNode<Context> script_context =
3569  LoadArrayElement(script_context_table, context_index.value());
3570  TNode<ScopeInfo> scope_info = CAST(
3571  LoadContextElementNoCell(script_context, Context::SCOPE_INFO_INDEX));
3572 
3573  TNode<IntPtrT> context_local_index =
3574  IndexOfLocalName(scope_info, name, &loop);
3575 
3576  TNode<IntPtrT> var_index = IntPtrAdd(
3577  IntPtrConstant(Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS), context_local_index);
3578  TNode<Object> result = LoadContextElement(script_context, var_index);
3579  GotoIf(IsTheHole(result), found_hole);
3580  Return(result);
3581  }
3582 }
3583 
3584 void AccessorAssembler::LoadGlobalIC_NoFeedback(TNode<Context> context,
3585  TNode<Object> name,
3586  TNode<Smi> smi_typeof_mode) {
3587  TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
3588  Label regular_load(this), throw_reference_error(this, Label::kDeferred);
3589 
3590  GotoIfNot(IsString(CAST(name)), &regular_load);
3591  ScriptContextTableLookup(CAST(name), native_context, &throw_reference_error,
3592  &regular_load);
3593 
3594  BIND(&throw_reference_error);
3595  Return(CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowReferenceError, context, name));
3596 
3597  BIND(&regular_load);
3598  TNode<JSGlobalObject> global_object =
3599  CAST(LoadContextElementNoCell(native_context, Context::EXTENSION_INDEX));
3600  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kLoadIC_NoFeedback, context, global_object, name,
3601  smi_typeof_mode);
3602 }
3603 
3604 void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadIC(const LoadICParameters* p,
3605  LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
3606  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3607 
3608  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3609  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
3610  try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
3611  try_uninitialized(this, Label::kDeferred),
3612  try_polymorphic_name(this, Label::kDeferred),
3613  miss(this, Label::kDeferred), generic(this, Label::kDeferred);
3614 
3615  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3616  LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object());
3617  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map), &miss);
3618 
3619  TryEnumeratedKeyedLoad(p, lookup_start_object_map, &direct_exit);
3620 
3621  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &generic);
3622 
3623  // Check monomorphic case.
3624  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_lookup_start_object_map =
3625  MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map);
3626  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(
3627  p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_lookup_start_object_map, &if_handler,
3628  &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3629  BIND(&if_handler);
3630  {
3631  LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3632  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(
3633  &lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit, ICMode::kNonGlobalIC,
3634  OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined, kSupportElements, access_mode);
3635  }
3636 
3637  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3638  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3639  {
3640  // Check polymorphic case.
3641  Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_polymorphic");
3642  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &try_megamorphic);
3643  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_lookup_start_object_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
3644  &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3645  }
3646 
3647  BIND(&try_megamorphic);
3648  {
3649  // Check megamorphic case.
3650  Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_megamorphic");
3651  Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()), &generic,
3652  &try_uninitialized);
3653  }
3654 
3655  BIND(&generic);
3656  {
3657  // TODO(jkummerow): Inline this? Or some of it?
3658  TailCallBuiltin(
3659  access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad ? Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_Megamorphic
3660  : Builtin::kKeyedHasIC_Megamorphic,
3661  p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3662  }
3663 
3664  BIND(&try_uninitialized);
3665  {
3666  // Check uninitialized case.
3667  Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_uninitialized");
3668  Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, UninitializedSymbolConstant()), &miss,
3669  &try_polymorphic_name);
3670  }
3671 
3672  BIND(&try_polymorphic_name);
3673  {
3674  // We might have a name in feedback, and a weak fixed array in the next
3675  // slot.
3676  Comment("KeyedLoadIC_try_polymorphic_name");
3677  TVARIABLE(Name, var_name);
3678  Label if_polymorphic_name(this), feedback_matches(this),
3679  if_internalized(this), if_notinternalized(this, Label::kDeferred);
3680 
3681  // Fast-case: The recorded {feedback} matches the {name}.
3682  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, p->name()), &feedback_matches);
3683 
3684  {
3685  // Try to internalize the {name} if it isn't already.
3686  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
3687  TryToName(p->name(), &miss, &var_index, &if_internalized, &var_name,
3688  &miss, &if_notinternalized);
3689  }
3690 
3691  BIND(&if_internalized);
3692  {
3693  // The {var_name} now contains a unique name.
3694  Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, var_name.value()),
3695  &if_polymorphic_name, &miss);
3696  }
3697 
3698  BIND(&if_notinternalized);
3699  {
3700  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
3701  TryInternalizeString(CAST(p->name()), &miss, &var_index, &if_internalized,
3702  &var_name, &miss, &miss);
3703  }
3704 
3705  BIND(&feedback_matches);
3706  {
3707  var_name = CAST(p->name());
3708  Goto(&if_polymorphic_name);
3709  }
3710 
3711  BIND(&if_polymorphic_name);
3712  {
3713  // If the name comparison succeeded, we know we have a weak fixed array
3714  // with at least one map/handler pair.
3715  TailCallBuiltin(access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad
3716  ? Builtin::kKeyedLoadIC_PolymorphicName
3717  : Builtin::kKeyedHasIC_PolymorphicName,
3718  p->context(), p->receiver(), var_name.value(), p->slot(),
3719  p->vector());
3720  }
3721  }
3722 
3723  BIND(&miss);
3724  {
3725  Comment("KeyedLoadIC_miss");
3726  TailCallRuntime(
3727  access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad ? Runtime::kKeyedLoadIC_Miss
3728  : Runtime::kKeyedHasIC_Miss,
3729  p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(), p->slot(), p->vector());
3730  }
3731 }
3732 
3733 void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadICGeneric(const LoadICParameters* p) {
3734  TVARIABLE(Object, var_name, p->name());
3735 
3736  Label if_runtime(this, Label::kDeferred);
3737  TNode<Object> lookup_start_object = p->lookup_start_object();
3738  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(lookup_start_object), &if_runtime);
3739  GotoIf(IsNullOrUndefined(lookup_start_object), &if_runtime);
3740 
3741  {
3742  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, var_index);
3743  TVARIABLE(Name, var_unique);
3744  Label if_index(this), if_unique_name(this, &var_name), if_notunique(this),
3745  if_other(this, Label::kDeferred);
3746 
3747  TryToName(var_name.value(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name,
3748  &var_unique, &if_other, &if_notunique);
3749 
3750  BIND(&if_unique_name);
3751  {
3752  LoadICParameters pp(p, var_unique.value());
3753  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3754  GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3755  LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map), &pp,
3756  &if_runtime);
3757  }
3758 
3759  BIND(&if_other);
3760  {
3761  var_name = CallBuiltin(Builtin::kToName, p->context(), var_name.value());
3762  TryToName(var_name.value(), &if_index, &var_index, &if_unique_name,
3763  &var_unique, &if_runtime, &if_notunique);
3764  }
3765 
3766  BIND(&if_notunique);
3767  {
3768  if (v8_flags.internalize_on_the_fly) {
3769  // Ideally we could return undefined directly here if the name is not
3770  // found in the string table, i.e. it was never internalized, but that
3771  // invariant doesn't hold with named property interceptors (at this
3772  // point), so we take the {if_runtime} path instead.
3773  Label if_in_string_table(this);
3774  TryInternalizeString(CAST(var_name.value()), &if_index, &var_index,
3775  &if_in_string_table, &var_unique, &if_runtime,
3776  &if_runtime);
3777 
3778  BIND(&if_in_string_table);
3779  {
3780  // TODO(bmeurer): We currently use a version of GenericPropertyLoad
3781  // here, where we don't try to probe the megamorphic stub cache
3782  // after successfully internalizing the incoming string. Past
3783  // experiments with this have shown that it causes too much traffic
3784  // on the stub cache. We may want to re-evaluate that in the future.
3785  LoadICParameters pp(p, var_unique.value());
3786  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map =
3787  LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3788  GenericPropertyLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object),
3789  lookup_start_object_map,
3790  LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map), &pp,
3791  &if_runtime, kDontUseStubCache);
3792  }
3793  } else {
3794  Goto(&if_runtime);
3795  }
3796  }
3797 
3798  BIND(&if_index);
3799  {
3800  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadMap(CAST(lookup_start_object));
3801  GenericElementLoad(CAST(lookup_start_object), lookup_start_object_map,
3802  LoadMapInstanceType(lookup_start_object_map),
3803  var_index.value(), &if_runtime);
3804  }
3805  }
3806 
3807  BIND(&if_runtime);
3808  {
3809  Comment("KeyedLoadGeneric_slow");
3810  // TODO(jkummerow): Should we use the GetProperty TF stub instead?
3811  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kGetProperty, p->context(),
3812  p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(), var_name.value());
3813  }
3814 }
3815 
3816 void AccessorAssembler::KeyedLoadICPolymorphicName(const LoadICParameters* p,
3817  LoadAccessMode access_mode) {
3818  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
3819  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3820 
3821  TNode<JSAny> lookup_start_object = p->lookup_start_object();
3822  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadReceiverMap(lookup_start_object);
3823  TNode<Name> name = CAST(p->name());
3824  TNode<FeedbackVector> vector = CAST(p->vector());
3825  TNode<TaggedIndex> slot = p->slot();
3826  TNode<Context> context = p->context();
3827 
3828  // When we get here, we know that the {name} matches the recorded
3829  // feedback name in the {vector} and can safely be used for the
3830  // LoadIC handler logic below.
3831  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32BinaryNot(IsDeprecatedMap(lookup_start_object_map)));
3832  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedEqual(name, LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot)),
3833  name, vector);
3834 
3835  // Check if we have a matching handler for the {lookup_start_object_map}.
3836  TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
3837  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot, kTaggedSize);
3838  TNode<WeakFixedArray> array = CAST(feedback_element);
3839  HandlePolymorphicCase(MakeWeak(lookup_start_object_map), array, &if_handler,
3840  &var_handler, &miss);
3841 
3842  BIND(&if_handler);
3843  {
3844  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3845  LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(p);
3846  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(
3847  &lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit, ICMode::kNonGlobalIC,
3848  OnNonExistent::kReturnUndefined, kOnlyProperties, access_mode);
3849  }
3850 
3851  BIND(&miss);
3852  {
3853  Comment("KeyedLoadIC_miss");
3854  TailCallRuntime(
3855  access_mode == LoadAccessMode::kLoad ? Runtime::kKeyedLoadIC_Miss
3856  : Runtime::kKeyedHasIC_Miss,
3857  context, p->receiver_and_lookup_start_object(), name, slot, vector);
3858  }
3859 }
3860 
3861 void AccessorAssembler::StoreIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
3862  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler,
3863  ReinterpretCast<MaybeObject>(SmiConstant(0)));
3864 
3865  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
3866  if_handler_from_stub_cache(this, &var_handler, Label::kDeferred),
3867  try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
3868  try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred), miss(this, Label::kDeferred),
3869  no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
3870 
3871  TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
3872  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(receiver_map), &miss);
3873 
3874  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
3875 
3876  // Check monomorphic case.
3877  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_receiver_map = MakeWeak(receiver_map);
3878  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
3879  TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_receiver_map,
3880  &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
3881  BIND(&if_handler);
3882  {
3883  Comment("StoreIC_if_handler");
3884  HandleStoreICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss,
3885  ICMode::kNonGlobalIC);
3886  }
3887 
3888  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
3889  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
3890  {
3891  // Check polymorphic case.
3892  Comment("StoreIC_try_polymorphic");
3893  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)), &try_megamorphic);
3894  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, CAST(strong_feedback), &if_handler,
3895  &var_handler, &miss);
3896  }
3897 
3898  BIND(&try_megamorphic);
3899  {
3900  // Check megamorphic case.
3901  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()), &miss);
3902 
3903  TryProbeStubCache(p->stub_cache(isolate()), p->receiver(), receiver_map,
3904  CAST(p->name()), &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
3905  }
3906 
3907  BIND(&no_feedback);
3908  {
3909  // TODO(v8:12548): refactor SetNamedIC as a subclass of StoreIC, which can
3910  // be called here and below when !p->IsDefineNamedOwn().
3911  auto builtin = p->IsDefineNamedOwn() ? Builtin::kDefineNamedOwnIC_NoFeedback
3912  : Builtin::kStoreIC_NoFeedback;
3913  TailCallBuiltin(builtin, p->context(), p->receiver(), p->name(),
3914  p->value());
3915  }
3916 
3917  BIND(&miss);
3918  {
3919  auto runtime = p->IsDefineNamedOwn() ? Runtime::kDefineNamedOwnIC_Miss
3920  : Runtime::kStoreIC_Miss;
3921  TailCallRuntime(runtime, p->context(), p->value(), p->slot(), p->vector(),
3922  p->receiver(), p->name());
3923  }
3924 }
