3926 void AccessorAssembler::StoreGlobalIC(const StoreICParameters* pp) {
3927  Label no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred), if_lexical_var(this),
3928  if_heapobject(this);
3929  GotoIf(IsUndefined(pp->vector()), &no_feedback);
3930 
3931  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_weak_ref =
3932  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(pp->vector()), pp->slot());
3933  Branch(TaggedIsSmi(maybe_weak_ref), &if_lexical_var, &if_heapobject);
3934 
3935  BIND(&if_heapobject);
3936  {
3937  Label try_handler(this), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
3938 
3939  // This branch also handles the "handler mode": the weak reference is
3940  // cleared, the feedback extra is the handler. In that case we jump to
3941  // try_handler. (See FeedbackNexus::ConfigureHandlerMode.)
3942  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsWeakOrCleared(maybe_weak_ref));
3943  TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell =
3944  CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_weak_ref, &try_handler));
3945 
3946  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
3947  StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(property_cell, pp->value(), &direct_exit,
3948  &miss);
3949 
3950  BIND(&try_handler);
3951  {
3952  Comment("StoreGlobalIC_try_handler");
3953  TNode<MaybeObject> handler =
3954  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(pp->vector()), pp->slot(), kTaggedSize);
3955 
3956  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(handler, UninitializedSymbolConstant()), &miss);
3957 
3958  DCHECK(pp->receiver_is_null());
3959  DCHECK(pp->flags_is_null());
3960  TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(pp->context());
3961  StoreICParameters p(pp->context(),
3962  CAST(LoadContextElementNoCell(
3963  native_context, Context::GLOBAL_PROXY_INDEX)),
3964  pp->name(), pp->value(), std::nullopt, pp->slot(),
3965  pp->vector(), StoreICMode::kDefault);
3966 
3967  HandleStoreICHandlerCase(&p, handler, &miss, ICMode::kGlobalIC);
3968  }
3969 
3970  BIND(&miss);
3971  {
3972  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreGlobalIC_Miss, pp->context(), pp->value(),
3973  pp->slot(), pp->vector(), pp->name());
3974  }
3975  }
3976 
3977  BIND(&if_lexical_var);
3978  {
3979  // This branch handles the "lexical variable mode": the feedback is a SMI
3980  // encoding the variable location. (See
3981  // FeedbackNexus::ConfigureLexicalVarMode.)
3982  Comment("Store lexical variable");
3983  TNode<IntPtrT> lexical_handler = SmiUntag(CAST(maybe_weak_ref));
3984  TNode<IntPtrT> context_index =
3985  Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::ContextIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3986  TNode<IntPtrT> slot_index =
3987  Signed(DecodeWord<FeedbackNexus::SlotIndexBits>(lexical_handler));
3988  TNode<Context> script_context =
3989  LoadScriptContext(pp->context(), context_index);
3990  StoreContextElement(script_context, slot_index, pp->value());
3991  Return(pp->value());
3992  }
3993 
3994  BIND(&no_feedback);
3995  {
3996  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreGlobalICNoFeedback_Miss, pp->context(),
3997  pp->value(), pp->name());
3998  }
3999 }
4000 
4001 void AccessorAssembler::StoreGlobalIC_PropertyCellCase(
4002  TNode<PropertyCell> property_cell, TNode<Object> value,
4003  ExitPoint* exit_point, Label* miss) {
4004  Comment("StoreGlobalIC_TryPropertyCellCase");
4005 
4006  // Load the payload of the global parameter cell. A hole indicates that
4007  // the cell has been invalidated and that the store must be handled by the
4008  // runtime.
4009  TNode<Object> cell_contents =
4010  LoadObjectField(property_cell, PropertyCell::kValueOffset);
4011  TNode<Int32T> details = LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(
4012  property_cell, PropertyCell::kPropertyDetailsRawOffset);
4013  GotoIf(IsSetWord32(details, PropertyDetails::kAttributesReadOnlyMask), miss);
4014  CSA_DCHECK(this,
4015  Word32Equal(DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::KindField>(details),
4016  Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyKind::kData))));
4017 
4018  TNode<Uint32T> type =
4019  DecodeWord32<PropertyDetails::PropertyCellTypeField>(details);
4020 
4021  Label constant(this), store(this), not_smi(this);
4022 
4023  GotoIf(Word32Equal(type, Int32Constant(
4024  static_cast<int>(PropertyCellType::kConstant))),
4025  &constant);
4026  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNotAnyHole(cell_contents));
4027 
4028  GotoIf(Word32Equal(
4029  type, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(PropertyCellType::kMutable))),
4030  &store);
4031  CSA_DCHECK(this,
4032  Word32Or(Word32Equal(type, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(
4033  PropertyCellType::kConstantType))),
4034  Word32Equal(type, Int32Constant(static_cast<int>(
4035  PropertyCellType::kUndefined)))));
4036 
4037  GotoIfNot(TaggedIsSmi(cell_contents), &not_smi);
4038  GotoIfNot(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
4039  Goto(&store);
4040 
4041  BIND(&not_smi);
4042  {
4043  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(value), miss);
4044  TNode<Map> expected_map = LoadMap(CAST(cell_contents));
4045  TNode<Map> map = LoadMap(CAST(value));
4046  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(expected_map, map), miss);
4047  Goto(&store);
4048  }
4049 
4050  BIND(&store);
4051  {
4052  StoreObjectField(property_cell, PropertyCell::kValueOffset, value);
4053  exit_point->Return(value);
4054  }
4055 
4056  BIND(&constant);
4057  {
4058  // Since |value| is never the hole, the equality check below also handles an
4059  // invalidated property cell correctly.
4060  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsNotAnyHole(value));
4061  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(cell_contents, value), miss);
4062  exit_point->Return(value);
4063  }
4064 }

4066 void AccessorAssembler::KeyedStoreIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
4067  Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4068  {
4069  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4070 
4071  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
4072  try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4073  try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4074  no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred),
4075  try_polymorphic_name(this, Label::kDeferred);
4076 
4077  TNode<Map> receiver_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
4078  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(receiver_map), &miss);
4079 
4080  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
4081 
4082  // Check monomorphic case.
4083  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_receiver_map = MakeWeak(receiver_map);
4084  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
4085  TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_receiver_map,
4086  &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
4087  BIND(&if_handler);
4088  {
4089  Comment("KeyedStoreIC_if_handler");
4090  HandleStoreICHandlerCase(p, var_handler.value(), &miss,
4091  ICMode::kNonGlobalIC, kSupportElements);
4092  }
4093 
4094  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
4095  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
4096  {
4097  // CheckPolymorphic case.
4098  Comment("KeyedStoreIC_try_polymorphic");
4099  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
4100  &try_megamorphic);
4101  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, CAST(strong_feedback),
4102  &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
4103  }
4104 
4105  BIND(&try_megamorphic);
4106  {
4107  // Check megamorphic case.
4108  Comment("KeyedStoreIC_try_megamorphic");
4109  Branch(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
4110  &no_feedback, &try_polymorphic_name);
4111  }
4112 
4113  BIND(&no_feedback);
4114  {
4115  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kKeyedStoreIC_Megamorphic, p->context(),
4116  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
4117  p->vector());
4118  }
4119 
4120  BIND(&try_polymorphic_name);
4121  {
4122  // We might have a name in feedback, and a fixed array in the next slot.
4123  Comment("KeyedStoreIC_try_polymorphic_name");
4124  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, p->name()), &miss);
4125  // If the name comparison succeeded, we know we have a feedback vector
4126  // with at least one map/handler pair.
4127  TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element =
4128  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(p->vector()), p->slot(), kTaggedSize);
4129  TNode<WeakFixedArray> array = CAST(feedback_element);
4130  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_receiver_map, array, &if_handler, &var_handler,
4131  &miss);
4132  }
4133  }
4134  BIND(&miss);
4135  {
4136  Comment("KeyedStoreIC_miss");
4137  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kKeyedStoreIC_Miss, p->context(), p->value(),
4138  p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4139  }
4140 }

4236 void AccessorAssembler::StoreInArrayLiteralIC(const StoreICParameters* p) {
4237  Label miss(this, Label::kDeferred), no_feedback(this, Label::kDeferred);
4238  {
4239  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4240 
4241  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler),
4242  try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
4243  try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred);
4244 
4245  TNode<Map> array_map = LoadReceiverMap(p->receiver());
4246  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(array_map), &miss);
4247 
4248  GotoIf(IsUndefined(p->vector()), &no_feedback);
4249 
4250  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_array_map = MakeWeak(array_map);
4251  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback =
4252  TryMonomorphicCase(p->slot(), CAST(p->vector()), weak_array_map,
4253  &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
4254 
4255  BIND(&if_handler);
4256  {
4257  Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_if_handler");
4258  // This is a stripped-down version of HandleStoreICHandlerCase.
4259  Label if_transitioning_element_store(this), if_smi_handler(this);
4260 
4261  // Check used to identify the Slow case.
4262  // Currently only the Slow case uses a Smi handler.
4263  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(var_handler.value()), &if_smi_handler);
4264 
4265  TNode<HeapObject> handler = CAST(var_handler.value());
4266  GotoIfNot(IsCode(handler), &if_transitioning_element_store);
4267 
4268  {
4269  // Call the handler.
4270  TNode<Code> code_handler = CAST(handler);
4271  TailCallStub(StoreWithVectorDescriptor{}, code_handler, p->context(),
4272  p->receiver(), p->name(), p->value(), p->slot(),
4273  p->vector());
4274  }
4275 
4276  BIND(&if_transitioning_element_store);
4277  {
4278  TNode<MaybeObject> maybe_transition_map =
4279  LoadHandlerDataField(CAST(handler), 1);
4280  TNode<Map> transition_map =
4281  CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(maybe_transition_map, &miss));
4282  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(transition_map), &miss);
4283  TNode<Code> code = CAST(
4284  LoadObjectField(handler, offsetof(StoreHandler, smi_handler_)));
4285  TailCallStub(StoreTransitionDescriptor{}, code, p->context(),
4286  p->receiver(), p->name(), transition_map, p->value(),
4287  p->slot(), p->vector());
4288  }
4289 
4290  BIND(&if_smi_handler);
4291  {
4292 #ifdef DEBUG
4293  // A check to ensure that no other Smi handler uses this path.
4294  TNode<Int32T> handler_word = SmiToInt32(CAST(var_handler.value()));
4295  TNode<Uint32T> handler_kind =
4296  DecodeWord32<StoreHandler::KindBits>(handler_word);
4297  CSA_DCHECK(this, Word32Equal(handler_kind, STORE_KIND(kSlow)));
4298 #endif
4299 
4300  Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_Slow");
4301  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreInArrayLiteralIC_Slow, p->context(),
4302  p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4303  }
4304  }
4305 
4306  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
4307  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
4308  {
4309  Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_try_polymorphic");
4310  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
4311  &try_megamorphic);
4312  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_array_map, CAST(strong_feedback), &if_handler,
4313  &var_handler, &miss);
4314  }
4315 
4316  BIND(&try_megamorphic);
4317  {
4318  Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_try_megamorphic");
4319  CSA_DCHECK(
4320  this,
4321  Word32Or(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, UninitializedSymbolConstant()),
4322  TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant())));
4323  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
4324  &miss);
4325  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreInArrayLiteralIC_Slow, p->context(),
4326  p->value(), p->receiver(), p->name());
4327  }
4328  }
4329 
4330  BIND(&no_feedback);
4331  {
4332  Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_NoFeedback");
4333  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCreateDataProperty, p->context(), p->receiver(),
4334  p->name(), p->value());
4335  }
4336 
4337  BIND(&miss);
4338  {
4339  Comment("StoreInArrayLiteralIC_miss");
4340  TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kStoreInArrayLiteralIC_Miss, p->context(),
4341  p->value(), p->slot(), p->vector(), p->receiver(),
4342  p->name());
4343  }
4344 }

4348 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLoadIC() {
4349  using Descriptor = LoadWithVectorDescriptor;
4350 
4351  auto receiver = Parameter<JSAny>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
4352  auto name = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName);
4353  auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
4354  auto vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
4355  auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
4356 
4357  LoadICParameters p(context, receiver, name, slot, vector);
4358  LoadIC(&p);
4359 }
4360 
4361 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLoadIC_Megamorphic() {
4362  using Descriptor = LoadWithVectorDescriptor;
4363 
4364  auto receiver = Parameter<JSAny>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
4365  auto name = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName);
4366  auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
4367  auto vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
4368  auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
4369 
4370  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
4371  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4372  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4373 
4374  CSA_DCHECK(
4375  this,
4376  Word32Or(
4377  Word32Or(
4378  // Either the IC is in regular megamorphic state...
4379  TaggedEqual(LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot),
4380  MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
4381  // ...or it's monomorphic but using a slow handler. Compilers are
4382  // free to approximate this by using the generic stub for
4383  // everything.
4384  TaggedEqual(
4385  LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot, kTaggedSize),
4386  SmiConstant(*LoadHandler::LoadSlow(isolate())))),
4387  TaggedEqual(LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(CAST(vector), slot, kTaggedSize),
4388  SmiConstant(LoadHandler::LoadGeneric()))));
4389 
4390  TryProbeStubCache(isolate()->load_stub_cache(), receiver, CAST(name),
4391  &if_handler, &var_handler, &miss);
4392 
4393  BIND(&if_handler);
4394  LazyLoadICParameters p(
4395  // lazy_context
4396  [=] { return context; }, receiver,
4397  // lazy_name
4398  [=] { return name; },
4399  // lazy_slot
4400  [=] { return slot; }, vector);
4401  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
4402 
4403  BIND(&miss);
4404  direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, context, receiver, name,
4405  slot, vector);
4406 }

4408 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLoadIC_Noninlined() {
4409  using Descriptor = LoadWithVectorDescriptor;
4410 
4411  auto receiver = Parameter<JSAny>(Descriptor::kReceiver);
4412  auto name = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName);
4413  auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
4414  auto vector = Parameter<FeedbackVector>(Descriptor::kVector);
4415  auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
4416 
4417  ExitPoint direct_exit(this);
4418  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
4419  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler), miss(this, Label::kDeferred);
4420 
4421  TNode<MaybeObject> feedback_element = LoadFeedbackVectorSlot(vector, slot);
4422  TNode<HeapObject> feedback = CAST(feedback_element);
4423 
4424  LoadICParameters p(context, receiver, name, slot, vector);
4425  TNode<Map> lookup_start_object_map = LoadReceiverMap(p.lookup_start_object());
4426  LoadIC_Noninlined(&p, lookup_start_object_map, feedback, &var_handler,
4427  &if_handler, &miss, &direct_exit);
4428 
4429  BIND(&if_handler);
4430  {
4431  LazyLoadICParameters lazy_p(&p);
4432  HandleLoadICHandlerCase(&lazy_p, var_handler.value(), &miss, &direct_exit);
4433  }
4434 
4435  BIND(&miss);
4436  direct_exit.ReturnCallRuntime(Runtime::kLoadIC_Miss, context, receiver, name,
4437  slot, vector);
4438 }

4572 
4573 void AccessorAssembler::LookupContext(LazyNode<Object> lazy_name,
4574  TNode<TaggedIndex> depth,
4575  LazyNode<TaggedIndex> lazy_slot,
4576  TNode<Context> context,
4577  TypeofMode typeof_mode,
4578  ContextMode context_mode) {
4579  Label slowpath(this, Label::kDeferred);
4580 
4581  // Check for context extensions to allow the fast path.
4582  TNode<Context> slot_context = GotoIfHasContextExtensionUpToDepth(
4583  context, Unsigned(TruncateWordToInt32(TaggedIndexToIntPtr(depth))),
4584  &slowpath);
4585 
4586  // Fast path does a normal load context.
4587  {
4588  auto slot = lazy_slot();
4589  Return(context_mode == ContextMode::kHasContextCells
4590  ? LoadContextElement(slot_context, TaggedIndexToIntPtr(slot))
4591  : LoadContextElementNoCell(slot_context,
4592  TaggedIndexToIntPtr(slot)));
4593  }
4594 
4595  // Slow path when we have to call out to the runtime.
4596  BIND(&slowpath);
4597  {
4598  auto name = lazy_name();
4599  Runtime::FunctionId function_id = typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kInside
4600  ? Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof
4601  : Runtime::kLoadLookupSlot;
4602  TailCallRuntime(function_id, context, name);
4603  }
4604 }
4605 
4606 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLookupContextTrampoline(
4607  TypeofMode typeof_mode, ContextMode context_mode) {
4608  using Descriptor = LookupTrampolineDescriptor;
4609  LookupContext([&] { return Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kName); },
4610  Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kDepth),
4611  [&] { return Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot); },
4612  Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext), typeof_mode,
4613  context_mode);
4614 }

4616 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateLookupContextBaseline(

4625 void AccessorAssembler::LookupGlobalIC(
4626  LazyNode<Object> lazy_name, TNode<TaggedIndex> depth,
4627  LazyNode<TaggedIndex> lazy_slot, TNode<Context> context,
4628  LazyNode<FeedbackVector> lazy_feedback_vector, TypeofMode typeof_mode) {
4629  Label slowpath(this, Label::kDeferred);
4630 
4631  // Check for context extensions to allow the fast path
4632  GotoIfHasContextExtensionUpToDepth(
4633  context, Unsigned(TruncateWordToInt32(TaggedIndexToIntPtr(depth))),
4634  &slowpath);
4635 
4636  // Fast path does a normal load global
4637  {
4638  TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::LoadGlobalICInOptimizedCode(typeof_mode), context,
4639  lazy_name(), lazy_slot(), lazy_feedback_vector());
4640  }
4641 
4642  // Slow path when we have to call out to the runtime
4643  BIND(&slowpath);
4644  Runtime::FunctionId function_id = typeof_mode == TypeofMode::kInside
4645  ? Runtime::kLoadLookupSlotInsideTypeof
4646  : Runtime::kLoadLookupSlot;
4647  TailCallRuntime(function_id, context, lazy_name());
4648 }

5101 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateCloneObjectIC_Slow() {
5102  using Descriptor = CloneObjectWithVectorDescriptor;
5103  auto source = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kSource);
5104  auto flags = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kFlags);
5105  auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
5106 
5107  // The CloneObjectIC_Slow implementation uses the same call interface as
5108  // CloneObjectIC, so that it can be tail called from it. However, the feedback
5109  // slot and vector are not used.
5110 
5111  // First try a fast case where we copy the properties with a CSA loop.
5112  Label try_fast_case(this), call_runtime(this, Label::kDeferred);
5113 
5114  // For SMIs and non JSObjects we use 0 in object properties.
5115  TVARIABLE(IntPtrT, number_of_properties, IntPtrConstant(0));
5116  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(source), &try_fast_case);
5117  {
5118  TNode<Map> source_map = LoadMap(CAST(source));
5119  // We still want to stay in the semi-fast case for oddballs, strings,
5120  // proxies and such. Therefore we continue here, but using 0 in object
5121  // properties.
5122  GotoIfNot(IsJSObjectMap(source_map), &try_fast_case);
5123 
5124  // At this point we don't know yet if ForEachEnumerableOwnProperty can
5125  // handle the source object. In case it is a dictionary mode object or has
5126  // non simple properties the latter will bail to `runtime_copy`. For code
5127  // compactness we don't check it here, assuming that the number of in-object
5128  // properties is set to 0 (or a reasonable value).
5129  number_of_properties = MapUsedInObjectProperties(source_map);
5130  GotoIf(IntPtrGreaterThanOrEqual(number_of_properties.value(),
5131  IntPtrConstant(JSObject::kMapCacheSize)),
5132  &call_runtime);
5133  }
5134  Goto(&try_fast_case);
5135 
5136  BIND(&try_fast_case);
5137  TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
5138  TNode<Map> initial_map = LoadCachedMap(
5139  native_context, number_of_properties.value(), &call_runtime);
5140  TNode<JSObject> result = AllocateJSObjectFromMap(initial_map);
5141 
5142  // Handle the case where the object literal overrides the prototype.
5143  {
5144  Label did_set_proto_if_needed(this);
5145  TNode<BoolT> is_null_proto = SmiNotEqual(
5146  SmiAnd(flags, SmiConstant(ObjectLiteral::kHasNullPrototype)),
5147  SmiConstant(Smi::zero()));
5148  GotoIfNot(is_null_proto, &did_set_proto_if_needed);
5149 
5150  CallRuntime(Runtime::kInternalSetPrototype, context, result,
5151  NullConstant());
5152 
5153  Goto(&did_set_proto_if_needed);
5154  BIND(&did_set_proto_if_needed);
5155  }
5156 
5157  // Early return for when we know there are no properties.
5158  ReturnIf(TaggedIsSmi(source), result);
5159  ReturnIf(IsNullOrUndefined(source), result);
5160 
5161  Label runtime_copy(this, Label::kDeferred);
5162 
5163  TNode<Map> source_map = LoadMap(CAST(source));
5164  GotoIfNot(IsJSObjectMap(source_map), &runtime_copy);
5165  // Takes care of objects with elements.
5166  GotoIfNot(IsEmptyFixedArray(LoadElements(CAST(source))), &runtime_copy);
5167 
5168  // TODO(olivf, chrome:1204540) This can still be several times slower than the
5169  // Babel translation. TF uses FastGetOwnValuesOrEntries -- should we do sth
5170  // similar here?
5171  ForEachEnumerableOwnProperty(
5172  context, source_map, CAST(source), kPropertyAdditionOrder,
5173  [=, this](TNode<Name> key, LazyNode<Object> value) {
5174  CreateDataProperty(context, result, key, value());
5175  },
5176  &runtime_copy);
5177  Return(result);
5178 
5179  // This is the fall-back case for the above fastcase, where we allocated an
5180  // object, but failed to copy the properties in CSA.
5181  BIND(&runtime_copy);
5182  CallRuntime(Runtime::kCopyDataProperties, context, result, source);
5183  Return(result);
5184 
5185  // Final fallback is to call into the runtime version.
5186  BIND(&call_runtime);
5187  Return(CallRuntime(Runtime::kCloneObjectIC_Slow, context, source, flags));
5188 }

5192 
5193  auto source = Parameter<Object>(Descriptor::kSource);
5194  auto flags = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kFlags);
5195  auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
5196 
5197  TNode<FeedbackVector> vector = LoadFeedbackVectorFromBaseline();
5198  TNode<Context> context = LoadContextFromBaseline();

5200  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCloneObjectIC, context, source, flags, slot,

5203 
5204 void AccessorAssembler::GenerateCloneObjectIC() {
5205  using Descriptor = CloneObjectWithVectorDescriptor;
5206  auto source = Parameter<JSAny>(Descriptor::kSource);
5207  auto flags = Parameter<Smi>(Descriptor::kFlags);
5208  auto slot = Parameter<TaggedIndex>(Descriptor::kSlot);
5209  auto maybe_vector = Parameter<HeapObject>(Descriptor::kVector);
5210  auto context = Parameter<Context>(Descriptor::kContext);
5211  TVARIABLE(Map, result_map);
5212  Label if_result_map(this, &result_map), if_empty_object(this),
5213  miss(this, Label::kDeferred), try_polymorphic(this, Label::kDeferred),
5214  try_megamorphic(this, Label::kDeferred), slow(this, Label::kDeferred);
5215 
5216  TNode<Map> source_map = LoadReceiverMap(source);
5217  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(source_map), &miss);
5218 
5219  GotoIf(IsUndefined(maybe_vector), &miss);
5220 
5221  TNode<HeapObjectReference> feedback;
5222  TNode<HeapObjectReference> weak_source_map = MakeWeak(source_map);
5223 
5224  // Decide if monomorphic or polymorphic, then dispatch based on the handler.
5225  {
5226  TVARIABLE(MaybeObject, var_handler);
5227  Label if_handler(this, &var_handler);
5228  feedback = TryMonomorphicCase(slot, CAST(maybe_vector), weak_source_map,
5229  &if_handler, &var_handler, &try_polymorphic);
5230 
5231  BIND(&try_polymorphic);
5232  TNode<HeapObject> strong_feedback = GetHeapObjectIfStrong(feedback, &miss);
5233  {
5234  Comment("CloneObjectIC_try_polymorphic");
5235  GotoIfNot(IsWeakFixedArrayMap(LoadMap(strong_feedback)),
5236  &try_megamorphic);
5237  HandlePolymorphicCase(weak_source_map, CAST(strong_feedback), &if_handler,
5238  &var_handler, &miss);
5239  }
5240 
5241  BIND(&try_megamorphic);
5242  {
5243  Comment("CloneObjectIC_try_megamorphic");
5244  CSA_DCHECK(
5245  this,
5246  Word32Or(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, UninitializedSymbolConstant()),
5247  TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant())));
5248  GotoIfNot(TaggedEqual(strong_feedback, MegamorphicSymbolConstant()),
5249  &miss);
5250  Goto(&slow);
5251  }
5252 
5253  BIND(&if_handler);
5254  Comment("CloneObjectIC_if_handler");
5255 
5256  // When the result of cloning the object is an empty object literal we store
5257  // a Smi into the feedback.
5258  GotoIf(TaggedIsSmi(var_handler.value()), &if_empty_object);
5259 
5260  // Handlers for the CloneObjectIC stub are weak references to the Map of
5261  // a result object.
5262  result_map = CAST(GetHeapObjectAssumeWeak(var_handler.value(), &miss));
5263  GotoIf(IsDeprecatedMap(result_map.value()), &miss);
5264  Goto(&if_result_map);
5265  }
5266 
5267  // Cloning with a concrete result_map.
5268  {
5269  BIND(&if_result_map);
5270  Comment("CloneObjectIC_if_result_map");
5271 
5272  TNode<Object> object = FastCloneJSObject(
5273  CAST(source), source_map, result_map.value(),
5274  [&](TNode<Map> map, TNode<HeapObject> properties,
5275  TNode<FixedArray> elements) {
5276  return UncheckedCast<JSObject>(AllocateJSObjectFromMap(
5277  map, properties, elements, AllocationFlag::kNone,
5278  SlackTrackingMode::kDontInitializeInObjectProperties));
5279  },
5280  true /* target_is_new */);
5281 
5282  Return(object);
5283  }
5284 
5285  // Case for when the result is the empty object literal. Can't be shared with
5286  // the above since we must initialize the in-object properties.
5287  {
5288  BIND(&if_empty_object);
5289  Comment("CloneObjectIC_if_empty_object");
5290  TNode<NativeContext> native_context = LoadNativeContext(context);
5291  TNode<Map> initial_map = LoadObjectFunctionInitialMap(native_context);
5292  TNode<JSObject> object =
5293  UncheckedCast<JSObject>(AllocateJSObjectFromMap(initial_map, {}, {}));
5294  Return(object);
5295  }
5296 
5297  BIND(&slow);
5298  {
5299  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCloneObjectIC_Slow, context, source, flags, slot,
5300  maybe_vector);
5301  }
5302 
5303  BIND(&miss);
5304  {
5305  Comment("CloneObjectIC_miss");
5306  TNode<HeapObject> map_or_result =
5307  CAST(CallRuntime(Runtime::kCloneObjectIC_Miss, context, source, flags,
5308  slot, maybe_vector));
5309  Label restart(this);
5310  GotoIf(IsMap(map_or_result), &restart);
5311  CSA_DCHECK(this, IsJSObject(map_or_result));
5312  Return(map_or_result);
5313 
5314  BIND(&restart);
5315  result_map = CAST(map_or_result);
5316  Goto(&if_result_map);
5317  }
5318 }

5369 void AccessorAssembler::BranchIfPrototypesHaveNoElements(
5370  TNode<Map> receiver_map, Label* definitely_no_elements,
5371  Label* possibly_elements) {
5372  TVARIABLE(Map, var_map, receiver_map);
5373  Label loop_body(this, &var_map);
5374  TNode<FixedArray> empty_fixed_array = EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
5375  TNode<NumberDictionary> empty_slow_element_dictionary =
5376  EmptySlowElementDictionaryConstant();
5377  Goto(&loop_body);
5378 
5379  BIND(&loop_body);
5380  {
5381  TNode<Map> map = var_map.value();
5382  TNode<HeapObject> prototype = LoadMapPrototype(map);
5383  GotoIf(IsNull(prototype), definitely_no_elements);
5384  TNode<Map> prototype_map = LoadMap(prototype);
5385  TNode<Uint16T> prototype_instance_type = LoadMapInstanceType(prototype_map);
5386 
5387  // Pessimistically assume elements if a Proxy, Special API Object,
5388  // or JSPrimitiveWrapper wrapper is found on the prototype chain. After this
5389  // instance type check, it's not necessary to check for interceptors or
5390  // access checks.
5391  Label if_custom(this, Label::kDeferred), if_notcustom(this);
5392  Branch(IsCustomElementsReceiverInstanceType(prototype_instance_type),
5393  &if_custom, &if_notcustom);
5394 
5395  BIND(&if_custom);
5396  {
5397  // For string JSPrimitiveWrapper wrappers we still support the checks as
5398  // long as they wrap the empty string.
5399  GotoIfNot(
5400  InstanceTypeEqual(prototype_instance_type, JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE),
5401  possibly_elements);
5402  TNode<Object> prototype_value =
5403  LoadJSPrimitiveWrapperValue(CAST(prototype));
5404  Branch(IsEmptyString(prototype_value), &if_notcustom, possibly_elements);
5405  }
5406 
5407  BIND(&if_notcustom);
5408  {
5409  TNode<FixedArrayBase> prototype_elements = LoadElements(CAST(prototype));
5410  var_map = prototype_map;
5411  GotoIf(TaggedEqual(prototype_elements, empty_fixed_array), &loop_body);
5412  Branch(TaggedEqual(prototype_elements, empty_slow_element_dictionary),
5413  &loop_body, possibly_elements);
5414  }
5415  }
5416 }
